title: Agency
description: Any state office or activity of the executive and judicial branches of state government, including state agencies, departments, offices, divisions, boards, commissions, institutions of higher education as defined in RCW 28B.10.016, and correctional and other types of institutions.

title: Amendments
description: A formal or official change made to a contract that adds, removes, or updates parts of the agreement such as performance period, pricing, scope adjustments, adds or removes products or services.

title: Automated Clearing House (ACH)
description: Electronic payments commonly referred to as direct deposit and automatic debit. ACH is a low cost, safe and green payment method utilized by most state agencies to take advantage of economies of scale by processing transactions in batches rather than sending each payment separately.

title: Apparent Successful Bidder
description: The lowest responsive and responsible Bidder as determined by the bid evaluation process and prior to Bidder negotiations.

title: Award (Procurement)
description: This is a phase within the contract life cycle. Activities include; the Competitive Solicitation procurement process; negotiating (where permissible) with successful bidders; and contract execution.

title: Bidder
description: An entity who submits a bid in response to a solicitation issued for goods or services by an agency of Washington state government.

title: Business Intelligence
description: A tool to transform business data into meaningful and useful information.

title: Buyer
description: See Purchaser

title: Budgetary Control
description: The establishment of budgets and the continuous comparison between actual and budgeted results.

title: Certified Women Owned Business
description: Proof of woman's status. Each woman owner of a business applying for certification shall submit with the application form a copy of her birth certificate, valid driver's license, or other document which shows that the owner is a woman. The final determination will be in the sole discretion of the office. Business must be able to independently perform the services necessary to fulfill the contract. Business must be: A for-profit business. A small business according to the U.S. Small Business Administration. Eligible owner(s) must: Be a U.S. Citizen or permanent resident. Own at least 51% of the business. Control managerial and day-to-day operations. Be female, African American, Hispanic American, Native American, Asian-Pacific American, or Subcontinent Asian American. Other individuals may be found to be socially and economically disadvantaged on a case-by-case basis.

title: Certified Minority Owned Business
description: Proof of minority status. Each minority owner of a business applying for certification who is visibly identifiable as a minority shall submit with the MWBE application form a photograph or copy of documentation containing the owner's photograph. Each minority owner who is not visibly identifiable as a minority shall submit a copy of his or her birth certificate, tribal enrollment papers, or other document which shows that the owner meets the definition of "minority" as set forth in these rules. The final determination will be in the sole discretion of the office. Business must be able to independently perform the services necessary to fulfill the contract. Business must be: A for-profit business. A small business according to the U.S. Small Business Administration. Eligible owner(s) must: Be a U.S. Citizen or permanent resident. Own at least 51% of the business. Control managerial and day-to-day operations. Be female, African American, Hispanic American, Native American, Asian-Pacific American, or Subcontinent Asian American. Other individuals may be found to be socially and economically disadvantaged on a case-by-case basis.

title: Click-Through Agreement
description: An legally binding electronic agreement with terms of service to be accepted with caution by the user in the middle of an installation process requiring the clicking of acceptance on-screen to proceed.

title: Certified Veteran's Owned Business
description: Veteran includes every person, who at the time he or she seeks the benefits of RCW 46.18.212, 46.18.235, 72.36.030, 41.04.010, 73.04.090, 73.08.010, 73.08.070, 73.08.080, or 43.180.250, has received an honorable discharge or received a discharge for medical reasons with an honorable record, where applicable, and who has served in at least one of the following capacities: As a member in any branch of the armed forces of the United States, including the national guard and armed forces reserves, and has fulfilled his or her initial military service obligation; As a member of the women's air forces service pilots; As a member of the armed forces reserves, national guard, or coast guard, and has been called into federal service by a presidential select reserve call-up for at least 180 cumulative days; As a civil service crewmember with service aboard a U.S. army transport service or U.S. naval transportation service vessel in oceangoing service from December 7, 1941, through December 31, 1946; As a member of the Philippine armed forces/scouts during the period of armed conflict from December 7, 1941, through August 15, 1945; or A United States documented merchant mariner with service aboard an oceangoing vessel operated by the department of defense, or its agents, from both June 25, 1950, through July 27, 1953, in Korean territorial waters and from August 5, 1964, through May 7, 1975, in Vietnam territorial waters, and who received a military commendation. To qualify as a veteran owned business, the veteran or service-member must control and own at least 51 percent of the business and the business must be legally operating in the state of Washington. (Control means the authority or ability to direct, regulate or influence day-to-day operations. If business is a 50/50 split or to learn more about becoming a certified veteran owned business.

title: Chart of Accounts (COA)
description: A chart of accounts (COA) is a financial organizational tool that provides a complete listing of every account in an accounting system. An account is a unique record for each type of asset, liability, equity, revenue and expense.

title: Competitive Solicitation
description: Means a documented formal process providing an equal and open opportunity to bidders and culminating in a selection based on predetermined criteria.

title: Complaint(Procurement)
description: Written notification from a vendor raising issues or concerns with the solicitation requirements and/or evaluation process in regard to an open competitive procurement.

title: Contract (Procurement)
description: A contract is a promise that is a legally enforceable agreement between two or more parties.

title: Customer (Procurement)
description:
Global Approved Definition

A person or agency that buys goods or services directly, based on delegated authority or through utilization of DES services.

EMEA Definition

A person or agency that buys goods or services directly, based on delegated authority.


APAC Definition

A person or agency that buys goods or services directly, based on delegated authority or through utilization of services.

title: Dashboard
description: A visually intuitive and easy to understand graphical representation of key performance indicator shown on a single screen.

title: Control Account
description: An account in the general ledger in which the aggregate of all debit and credit postings to a number of related accounts (called the subsidiary accounts) are recorded. For example, the Accounts Receivable account is a control account supported by the aggregate of the individual customer subsidiary accounts.

title: Direct Buy
description: An established dollar threshold in which agencies may acquire goods and services directly from a vendor without requiring a competitive process. In the absence of an existing qualified master contract, agencies are authorized to purchase goods and services up to a cost of $10,000 (excluding sales tax) directly from a vendor and without competition. In addition, agencies are authorized to purchase goods and services up to a cost of $13,000 (excluding sales tax) directly from a vendor and without competition if the purchase is being made from a microbusiness, mini-business, or small business as those terms are defined by RCW 39.26.010 (19), (20) and (21).

title: Direct Debit
description: Method to make a payment directly from a bank account using an Automated Clearing House (ACH).

title: Emergency
description: A set of unforeseen circumstances beyond the control of the agency that either: (a) Presents a real, immediate, and extreme threat to the proper performance of essential functions; or (b) May reasonably be expected to result in material loss or damage to property, bodily injury, or loss of life, if immediate action is not taken.

title: DUNS Number - Data Universal Numbering System
description: Created in 1962, the Data Universal Numbering System or D-U-N-S® Number is D&B's copyrighted, proprietary means of identifying business entities on a location-specific basis.Assigned and maintained solely by D&B, this unique nine-digit identification number has been assigned to over 100 million businesses worldwide. A D-U-N-S® Number remains with the company location to which it has been assigned even if it closes or goes out-of-business. D-U-N-S® Number also "unlocks" a wealth of value-added data associated with that entity, including the business name, physical and mailing addresses, tradestyles ("doing business as"), principal names, financial, payment experiences,industry classifications (SICs and NAICS), socio-economic status,government data. The D-U-N-S® Number also links members of corporate family trees worldwide.

title: End-user
description: Person or organization that actually uses a product, as opposed to the person or organization that authorizes, orders, procures, or pays for it.

title: Encumbrance
description: An encumbrance is a reservation of an expenditure authority for obligations or contracts for goods, materials, and/or services, which have been ordered and are expected to be received before the expenditure authority lapses. Encumbrance accounting is only used in accounts subject to allotment. Encumbrance accounting ensures that expenditure authority will be available for recording the expenditure when the goods, materials or services are subsequently received. An agency may not obligate or encumber funds in excess of its expenditure authority. An encumbrance represents a commitment. It is not an expenditure.

title: Enterprise resource planning (ERP)
description: Enterprise resource planning (ERP) is the integrated management of common business practices across the enterprise and the technology that supports them. A complete ERP system combines data on an organization's main resources and provides decision makers with real time, enterprise information.

title: Enterprise
description: Encompassing the entire state of Washington as a single organization, rather than separate groups, departments, agencies or functions.

title: Four-way match
description: A process in accounts payable where the invoice from the vendor is matched against the purchase order, the shipping documents, and the quantity and price tolerance defined, before it is posted. The goal is to highlight any discrepancies in the purchasing process in order to save agencies from overspending or paying for an item that they did not receive.

title: Information Technology
description: All electronic technology systems, products and services.

title: Indirect Cost
description: Costs incurred for a common or joint purpose benefitting more than one cost objective, and not readily assignable to the cost objectives specifically benefitted, without effort disproportionate to the results achieved.

title: Key performance indicator
description: Key performance indicator (KPI) is a measurable value that demonstrates how effectively a company is achieving key business objectives. Organizations use KPIs to evaluate their success at reaching targets.

title: Interagency Agreements (IAAs)
description: An agreement between government agencies, entities or departments that defines cooperative work or services to be performed between them. The agreement defines the parties involved, the work performed and the transfer of resources, technologies and funds.

title: Master Contract
description: A statewide Contract for goods and/or services competitively awarded by an authorized Agency for use by other entities.

title: Market Research
description: An informal organized effort to gather information about target markets or customers to help determine course of action, eg RFI.

title: Master Contract Direct Buy
description: A procurement from a two-tier master contract where the second tier competition is not required due to the dollar value being below the direct buy threshold.

title: Matching
description: Matching is a control procedure used in accounts payable to ensure that the goods being paid for have been previously authorized. Matching determines the relationship between two or more accounting documents in the accounts payable solution: purchase orders (POs), invoices (or credit memos), and receipts. These documents are compared, either manually or through automated processes, to determine whether or not an invoice should be paid and, if so, what amount should be paid.

title: Master Contract Procurement
description: A procurement from a master contract

title: Micro Business
description: Microbusiness means any business entity, including a sole proprietorship, corporation, partnership, or other legal entity, that: (a) Is owned and operated independently from all other businesses; and (b) has a gross revenue of less than one million dollars annually as reported on its federal tax return or on its return filed with the department of revenue.

title: Mini Business
description: Mini business means any business entity, including a sole proprietorship, corporation, partnership, or other legal entity, that: (a) Is owned and operated independently from all other businesses; and (b) has a gross revenue of less than three million dollars, but one million dollars or more annually as reported on its federal tax return or on its return filed with the department of revenue.

title: Office of Minority and Women's Owned Business Enterprises (OMWBE)
description: RCW 39.19.010 Intent. The legislature finds that minority and women-owned businesses are significantly under-represented and have been denied equitable competitive opportunities in contracting. It is the intent of this chapter to mitigate societal discrimination and other factors in participating in public works and in providing goods and services and to delineate a policy that an increased level of participation by minority and women-owned and controlled businesses is desirable at all levels of state government. The purpose and intent of this chapter are to provide the maximum practicable opportunity for increased participation by minority and women-owned and controlled businesses in participating in public works and the process by which goods and services are procured by state agencies and educational institutions from the private sector.

title: Positive Pay
description: An automated fraud detection tool offered by most banks. In its simplest form, it is a service that matches the account number, check number and dollar amount of each check presented for payment against a list of checks previously authorized and issued by the agency. All three components of the check must match exactly or it will not pay.

title: Purchase
description: The Acquisition of goods or services, including the leasing or renting of goods.

title: OMWBE Certified
description: Certification of business enterprises. The office shall be the sole authority to perform certification of minority business enterprises, socially and economically disadvantaged business enterprises, and women's business enterprises throughout the state of Washington. Certification by the state office will allow these firms to participate in programs for these enterprises administered by the state of Washington, any city, town, county, special purpose district, public corporation created by the state, municipal corporation, or quasi-municipal corporation within the state of Washington. This statewide certification process will prevent duplication of effort, achieve efficiency, and permit local jurisdictions to further develop, implement, and/or enhance comprehensive systems of monitoring and compliance for contracts issued by their agencies.

title: Procurement
description: The process of obtaining or buying goods and services consistent with RCW 39.26 with the intent to Purchase.

title: Purchase Order (PO)
description: (A16) - A document that authorizes the delivery of specified merchandise or the rendering of certain services. This form is used by agencies to encumber, liquidate, and authorize payment for such purchase requisition requests.

title: Procurement Professional
description: A state employee possessing the knowledge, skills, and abilities through training and education who is able to develop and draft transactionally relevant procurement and contract documents to support agency operations.

title: Purchaser
description: An agency that purchases or acquires goods and/or services.

title: Small Business
description: Small business means an in-state business, including a sole proprietorship, corporation, partnership, or other legal entity, that: (a) Certifies, under penalty of perjury, that it is owned and operated independently from all other businesses and has either: (i) Fifty or fewer employees; or (ii) A gross revenue of less than seven million dollars annually as reported on its federal income tax return or its return filed with the department of revenue over the previous three consecutive years; or (b) Is certified with the office of women and minority business enterprises under chapter 39.19 RCW.

title: Sole Source
description: A contractor providing goods or services of such a unique nature or sole availability at the location required that the contractor is clearly and justifiably the only practicable source (best source) to provide the goods or services. Refers to a procurement situation where the goods or services are of such a unique nature or sole availability at the location required that one vendor is clearly and justifiably the only practicable source to provide the goods or services.

title: Vendor
description: An entity that provides goods and/or services.

title: Purchase Requisition
description: (A15) - A form used by agencies to request the Department of Enterprise Services, to order materials, supplies, and equipment, or to request an amendment of a previous requisition.

title: Accident Year
description: The year in which the accident took place and is used commonly in claims-related data and calculations.

title: Solicitation
description: See: Competitive Solicitation

title: Accident Year - Account
description: Automatically generated

title: Three-way match
description: A process in accounts payable where the invoice from the vendor is matched against the purchase order and shipping documents before it is posted. The goal is to highlight any discrepancies in the purchasing process in order to save agencies from overspending or paying for an item that they did not receive.

title: Accident Year - Expense Group
description: Automatically generated

title: Workflow
description: A workflow is approval routing for a process. When there is an approval needed, the system will sent it to the appropriate assigned person to approve before moving onto the next step.

title: Account Balance
description: The total sum of money in a particular bank account at a point in time, including debit and credit amounts.

title: Account
description: A Continuing relationship between the enterprise and another party, instantiated through an agreement and managed within a framework of established rules and procedures.

title: Account Value
description: The total value of an account or sum of multiple accounts.

title: Account Statement
description: A record of financial transactions, in relation to debit and credit accounts, held by a person or business over a given period of time.

title: Accounts Payable
description: A list of short term liabilities in which an organization or individual owes money to vendors for particular products or services that have been received or rendered but not paid to creditors.

title: Accretion
description: In reference to discount bonds, the process in which bonds are sold below face value and mature at par.

title: Accrual Basis
description: An accounting method in which investors, economists and businessmen count the number of days in a month or a year(s) (e.g. 30/360) to measure the performance and position of a company.

title: Accrual Bond
description: A bond that does not pay periodic interest payments, but is accrued and then added on at the time of maturity.

title: Accumulator
description: A type of security on which the investment return of an initial principal amount is reinvested, but the interest is not paid to the investor on the basis of that time period.

title: Accrued Interest
description: The interest that has accumulated on an investment, but has not yet been paid.

title: Adoption Taxpayer Identification Number (ATIN)
description: A temporary identification number issued by the IRS to individuals who are in the process of legally adopting a U.S. citizen or resident but who cannot get a Social Security Number (SSN) for that child in time to file their tax return.

title: Activity
description: An activity represents an action that is part of a business process. They are executed either by parties or by software applications.

title: Agreement Feature
description: Represents a portion of an agreement as related to the agreement's composition and structure. E.g: Clauses, options, benefits, services, ratings

title: Appraisal
description: An expert estimate of an asset's value or the extent of damage incurred provided by an impartial appraiser. Appraisals are typically performed either to set an asset's value for a loan/insurance transaction or when there is disagreement between parties.

title: Application
description: See Insurance Application or Software Application.

title: Archive
description: Original data that is no longer actively used and must be retained for certain business, legal, regulatory or technical purposes.

title: Archiving
description: The act of moving inactive data to another storage system.

title: Architecture
description: See Data Architecture.

title: Assessment
description: Any evaluation occurring at a given place or time. This often involves any one or more of the following: (1) an expert opinion (2) use of specialized instrumentation (3) use of analytical systems.

title: Area Code
description: A three-digit number that identifies one of the telephone service regions into which the US, Canada, and certain other countries are divided and that is dialed when calling from one area code to another.

title: Audit
description: Formal inspection and verification to check whether a standard or set of guidelines is being followed, records are accurate, or efficiency and effectiveness targets are being met.

title: Authoritative Data
description: Data elements or pieces of information that are endorsed by an appropriate set of governance entities as valid or trusted.

title: Assisted Conversion Rate
description: The sum of new policies quoted in the channel of interest and written in any channel for a product, divided by the number of total quote events in the channel of interest for a product.

title: Authoritative Source
description: A managed repository of valid or trusted data that is recognized by an appropriate set of governance entities and supports the governance entityís business environment.

title: Average Balance
description: The average of the closing balances for each day in a given month or statement period.

title: Auditable Business Unit (ABU)
description: Organizational unit responsible for managing a particular set or subset of enterprise data by line of business or data type.

title: Automated Teller Machines (ATMs)
description: Machines that conduct electronic transactions, such as withdrawing cash or depositing checks, by inserting a special card held by the account owner.

title: Beneficiary
description: Automatically generated

title: Batch Processing
description: The running of jobs that can run without end user interaction, or can be scheduled to run as resources permit.

title: Birth Date
description: See Date of Birth.

title: Budget
description: An itemized plan of a company's income and expenses expected for some period (i.e. annually or quarterly) in the future.

title: Billing Cycle
description: An interval of time, lasting about 25 days, during which bills are prepared.

title: Borrower
description: A person or entity that obtains funds from a business or individual for a specified period of time upon condition of promising to repay the loan.

title: Brand
description: A set of perceptions and images that represent a company and the products offered; the essence or promise of what will be delivered or experienced.

title: Bulk Material
description: Material ordered, stored, issued, and sold by weight (such as bar stock or minerals), volume (such as cement or oil), or footage (such as lumber).

title: Business Day Calendar Date
description: The specific corresponding calendar date for a business day.

title: Business Function
description: A process or operation that is performed routinely to carry out a part of the mission of an organization.

title: Business Sector Warehouse
description: A data warehouse solution dedicated to any number of business sectors (units).

title: Business Transformation & Technology Committee (BTTC)
description: A working committee of the board focused on risk and emerging technology.†

title: Business Rule
description: A statement that defines or constrains some aspect of the business. Intended to identify business structure or to control or influence the behavior of the organization.

title: Business Sector
description: A grouping of business lines according to business relationship category. Sectors are mutually exclusive with no overlapping business lines.

title: Cash Reserve
description: Total amount of cash kept on hand that can be withdrawn quickly to meet emergency funding needs.

title: Cancel Rewrite
description: Process that handles a pair of transactions to terminate a current policy and replace it with an equivalent policy for a P&C customer. Used when a significant alteration to a policy is needed, such as form, underwriting company or effective period.

title: Certificate of Deposit (CD)
description: An interest-bearing deposit account that is typically associated with longer-term savings. Allows customers to choose how long they would like to hold the CD, from 3 months to 60 months.

title: Cardholder Agreement
description: A written statement that describes in detail all the terms and conditions associated with a credit card.

title: Checking Account / Demand Deposit Account (DDA)
description: A transactional or liquid deposit account that allows for unlimited withdrawals and deposit of funds. Money held in a checking account can be withdrawn by various channels such as Automated Teller Machine (ATM), Web or Branch Office.

title: Change Data Capture
description: A set of software design patterns in databases used to determine and track the data that has changed so that action can be taken using the changed data. It is also an approach to data integration that is based on the identification, capture and delivery o

title: Change in Original Pending Coverage Count
description: Automatically generated

title: Clause
description: A provision of an insurance contract, or an endorsement to the policy.

title: Claim
description: A request for payment under an insurance contract for damages resulting from an insured event.

title: Co-borrower
description: An additional signing party whose income and credit history are used to help in the qualification of a loan, and is equally responsible for repayment of that loan.

title: Consumer Credit
description: A debt that someone incurs for the purpose of purchasing a good or service.

title: Control
description: Specific, systematic measure taken by an organization to ensure adherence to standards and policy. May be instituted to ensure data quality, safeguard assets and resources, mitigate risk, detect errors, or any combination thereof.

title: Credit Card Issue Date
description: The date a credit card account was opened.

title: Credit Card Number
description: The set of digits displayed on a credit card, used to identify both the credit card issuer and the account holder.

title: Conversion Rate
description: Count of new policies sold in the given period divided by the number of quote events counted in the given period.

title: Crafted Item
description: All types of items that are not manufactured or based on a model specification. These items tend to be handmade and of some significant value.

title: Credit Card Payment Network
description: The computer system companies that process credit card transactions. They provide a variety of benefits such as caps on limited liability if a card is lost or stolen and the ability to charge back damaged merchandise.

title: Credit Card Spend
description: Credit card purchases, cash advances and balance transfers. Net credit card spend excludes chargebacks, fraud losses, and returns.

title: Credit Card
description: An unsecured lending arrangement in the form of "Plastic Card" between holder and financial institution that allows the holder of the plastic card to purchase goods or services on credit. There are several types of credit cards, e.g., Visa¬Æ, MasterCard¬

title: Credit Risk
description: The risk that an issuer will fail to meet financial obligations in accordance with the agreed terms.

title: Criminal Event
description: An event that is an infraction of the law (e.g.,burglary, fraud, car-jacking, sabotage, theft, vandalism).

title: Credit Limit
description: Maximum amount of credit that a financial institution grants.

title: Cross-Sell Quote Event
description: A quote event for an existing P&C customer who owns a different personal lines product than the one being quoted.

title: Credit Risk Category
description: A matrix determined by risk associated procedures measuring factors like inherent risk, risk management, composite risk, and risk trends.

title: Customer Relationship Management (CRM)
description: A business strategy that aims to understand, anticipate and manage the response to the needs of an enterprise‚Äôs most important asset‚Äîits potential, current, and former customers and/or business partners.

title: Data Aggregation
description: The compiling of information from databases with intent to prepare combined datasets for data processing.

title: Data Architecture
description: A formal approach to creating and managing the flow and processing of data across IT systems and applications. Includes rules, policies, standards, and models.

title: Data Asset
description: A piece of information that contains valuable records. Can be a database, a document or any type of information that is managed as a single entity.

title: Critical Data Element (CDE)
description: The data elements essential to support accurate information needed for critical business processes and decisions.

title: Customer Service Representative (CSR)
description: Person responsible for maintaining goodwill between a business organization and its customers by answering questions, solving problems, and providing advice or assistance in utilizing the services of the organization.

title: Data Analytics
description: The process of inspecting, cleansing, transforming and modeling data with the goal of discovering useful information, suggesting conclusions, and supporting decision-making.

title: Data Custodians
description: Responsible for ensuring the veracity of the source data or authoritative data source and for defining data rules to ensure that the source data that has been remediated remains clean. Acts as data integration owner.

title: Data Decision
description: Agreement on how to resolve a specific data issue.

title: Data Governance (DG)
description: Data Governance is a collection of practices and processes which help to ensure the formal management of data assets within an organization.

title: Data Cleansing
description: The process of detecting and correcting or removing corrupt or inaccurate records from a record set, table, or database and refers to identifying incomplete, incorrect, inaccurate or irrelevant parts of the data and then replacing, modifying, or deleting

title: Data Governance Process
description: A defined way of accomplishing a data governance task. Supports data governance policy and standards, and can be broken down into step-by-step procedures.

title: Data Governance Policy
description: A set of high-level, enforceable standards used to govern data across the enterprise.

title: Data Lifecycle
description: Runs from the creation of data assets through their useful life in the business and eventual archival or destruction.

title: Data Governance Procedure
description: Step-by-step instructions for implementing the data governance policy and standards, outlining required processes and interactions between data governance teams, business partners, and systems.

title: Data Governance Standard
description: Specific mandatory control that outlines detailed, measurable requirements for compliance with the policy.

title: Data Quality Rule
description: Rules that evaluate or validate specific conditions associated with data sources. Can be used to extend data profiling analyses, test and evaluate data quality, or improve understanding of data integration requirements.

title: Data Lineage
description: The path a field's value takes between the system of record and the end point, including all locations and alterations made along the pathway.

title: Data Quality
description: A measure of data against its requirements. Aspects of data quality include accuracy, completeness, conformity, integrity, consistency, duplication, and timeliness.

title: Data Stakeholder
description: Those who use, affect, or are affected by data.

title: Data Standard
description: See Data Governance Standard

title: Data Steward
description: Business data governance lead who acts as the single point of contact between the business and the Enterprise Data Office (EDO).

title: Date of Birth
description: The month, day, and year a person was born.

title: Data Transformation
description: The process in computing of converting data from one format or structure into another format or structure. It is a fundamental aspect of most data integration[1] and data management tasks such as data wrangling, data warehousing, data integration and appl

title: Debt Consolidation Loan
description: A loan offered by a bank or lending institution replacing multiple loans with a single loan often with a lower monthly payment, but longer repayment period.

title: Data Warehouse
description: A storage architecture designed to hold data extracted from transactional systems, operational data stores and external sources.

title: Debt Recovery
description: Process initiated by a bank or lending institution recovering money not paid on time through procedures like debt settlement or selling of collaterals.

title: Data Wrangling
description: The process of transforming and mapping data from one raw data form into another format with the intent of making it more appropriate and valuable for a variety of downstream purposes such as analytics. A data wrangler is a person who performs these trans

title: Demographic Data
description: A statistical view of a population based on inherent traits such as gender, income, age, education, location and occupation. Typically personally identifiable information (PII).

title: Deposit Account
description: An account held with a bank or financial institution to deposit funds securely and to access the funds on-demand via various channels such as ATMs, Web or Branch Office.

title: Debt Repayment
description: The process of paying back debt borrowed from a lender including any accrued interest.

title: Disbursement Code - Accounts other than Departmental Expense
description: Automatically generated

title: Direct Agent (DA)
description: Automatically generated

title: Disbursement Code - Departmental Expenses
description: Automatically generated

title: Driver's License Number
description: A specific identification number assigned to a license issued under governmental authority that permits the holder to operate a motor vehicle.

title: Dynamic Data Masking
description: Masking of production data by obscuring original data with random characters such as substituting (*) yet preserving the data. Data will be visible based on a "Need-to-know" and least privilege.

title: Doing Business As (DBA)
description: Automatically generated

title: EInteraction
description: A subject area of the enterprise data warehouse (EDW) that houses details of interactions throughout their lifecycle.

title: Earning Assets
description: An investment capable of generating returns, either in the form of returns, interest, or cash.

title: Email Address
description: A name that identifies an electronic mailbox on a network where an email can be delivered. The electronic mail (email, e-mail) address used to reach someone via email. The format of an email address is user@domain.

title: Enterprise Data Warehouse (EDW)
description: Data repository consisting of data extracted from transaction systems, operational data stores and external sources. This data is aggregated and arranged into subject areas for use in enterprise-wide data analysis and reporting.

title: Employer Identification Number (EIN)

description: More commonly referred to as "Specs”. A part of the construction documents contained in the project manual consisting of written requirements for materials, equipment, construction systems, standards and workmanship.

title: Reflective Ceiling Drawing
description: Drawing that is a view looking straight up at the building’s ceiling and lighting plan.

title: As-built Drawings
description: Drawings that accurately reflect the changes in a building’s design as it was built.

title: Elevation
description: Elevation drawings are horizontal views of the building’s exterior taken from a perpendicular point of view.

title: Floor Plan
description: Drawing that is a view looking straight down after a horizontal plane is cut approximately 4’ above the floor.

title: Site Plan
description: Drawing that is a view looking straight down at the building illustrating its location and orientation on a plot of land.

title: Section
description: Drawing that is a horizontal view of the building after a vertical plane is cut through significant spaces of the building. The drawing will give user a sense of space and thickness of floors, ceilings and walls.

title: Specifications
description: More commonly referred to as "Specs”. A part of the construction documents contained in the project manual consisting of written requirements for materials, equipment, construction systems, standards and workmanship.

title: Battery Back Up
description: Back up system used to power emergency lights, life-safety system and other essential services when power goes out!!

title: Conduit
description: Wiring that distributes electricity to all aspects of electrical system

title: Cover Plates
description: Cover over electrical units such as outlets and junction boxes not in use.

title: Diffusers
description: Part of light fixture used to spread light out evenly from fixture.

title: Distribution Panel (DP)
description: Main switchboard that controls and protects the main feeder lines into a building. Distributes large incoming power into smaller parcels.

title: Electrical Panel
description: Panels that control branch circuits. Fuses or circuit breakers are located in this panel and used when individual circuits are tripped.

title: Fixture
description: Something that is permanently "fixed” to the building. Examples of fixtures related to the electrical system are outlets, overhead lighting units, etc.

title: GFI Receptacles
description: Ground Fault Interrupters receptacles (outlet) used in areas where power needs to be turned off quickly in case of shock potential. Used especially around water sources.

title: Junction Box
description: Also referred to as a J-box. Box is used to connect fixtures to circuitry.

title: Tripped Circuit
description: Circuit that was overloaded resulting in a blown fuse or tripped breaker. Problem can be eliminated by determining how students are overloading circuit and reducing the load. After load is reduced, fuse should be replaced or circuit breaker flipped back to the "on” position.

title: Caulking
description: Waterproof material used to seal building exterior to reduce outside weather from permeating interior. Typically used to seal windows and doors.

title: Channeling (Wall or Floor)
description: Act of cutting a trench through wall or floor material to place items such as conduit or piping. Channel is then filled in to cover over the hole.

title: Concrete
description: Building material containing a mixture of cement, aggregate (small stones, particles), and water. By itself, works very well in compression but steel reinforcement is needed on projects affected by tension and compression loads.

title: Door Closer
description: Piece of door hardware that is used to close door automatically after door is opened.

title: Door Strikes
description: Door hardware where door latch enters the doorframe.

title: Dry Wall
description: Application of gypsum board to wall.

title: Expansion Joint
description: Separation between material to allow for expansion or contraction due to temperature, moisture, etc.

title: Face Brick
description: Masonry brick used on exterior of building.

title: Framing
description: The skeletal structural units that make up the basic components that hold a structure up. Term typically used in wood construction.

title: Glazing
description: Plastic used in place of glass in a window.

title: Gypsum Board
description: A non-combustible board with a gypsum (calcium sulfate) core enclosed in tough, smooth paper.

title: Hardware
description: Material necessary to enable building doors to operate effectively.

title: Louver
description: An arrangement of metal blades to provide air slots that will permit airflow.

title: Masonry
description: A built-up construction or combination of masonry units bonded together with mortar. Masonry units include brick, concrete block (solid and hollow), glass block, etc.

title: Plaster
description: A finishing substance to cover walls.

title: Terrazzo
description: Floor finish containing two parts marble chips to one part portland cement. Color pigment may be added and material is polished.

title: VCT
description: Vinyl tile for floor covering. Material is very resilient and durable.

title: Boiler
description: A tank that is used to heat water for building or unit that stores hot water.

title: Chase (Pipe)
description: Areas furrowed into building for pipes to traverse structure without being visible. Typically, piping is accessible through removable access panels.

title: Ductwork
description: An arrangement of sheet-metal ducts to distribute supply air, return air and exhaust air.

title: Fan Coil
description: Heating and cooling unit.

title: Fixture
description: Something that is permanently "fixed” to the building. Examples of fixtures related to plumbing are faucets, tubs and toilets.

title: HVAC
description: "Heating, Ventilation and Air-Conditioning”- System that is responsible for the building’s climate control.

title: Hydraulics
description: Science that deals with the use and flow of water.

title: Risers/Stacks
description: Vertical Pipes in building. Separate risers/ stacks are used for supplying fresh water and removing wastewater.

title: Shower Base
description: One piece, pre-cast unit placed in bottom of shower unit.

title: Valve
description: Device incorporated into pipelines to control the flow of water into, through and from them. Valves are placed to control water at individual fixtures, risers, branches and buildings.

title: Valve Tags
description: Tag used by plumbers to identify what part of the plumbing system is controlled by the valve.

title: Vents
description: Pipes that permit gas to escape piping system and admit fresh air into pipes.

title: Footing
description: Structural member located at base of foundation used to spread building’s weight out over a large area of ground and prevent the building from sinking.

title: "I” Beam
description: Structural steel identified by its cross sectional characteristic.

title: Joist
description: Beams arranged parallel from wall to wall in a structure to support floor or ceiling.

title: Lintel
description: Structural member used to carry load over opening. Typically, used over window or door opening.

title: Rebar
description: Shortened terminology for "deformed steel bars for concrete reinforcement”. Steel rebars are placed in patterns depending on the load being held up and concrete is pour over the steel. The concrete and steel act as one structural system to handle loads in tension and compression.

title: Retaining Wall
description: Wall used to keep a material or substance out of a space.

title: Shoring
description: Formwork used to stabilize and add additional support to structure during facilities improvement project.

title: Slab
description: Concrete floor system. Types of slabs include one-way, and two-way systems.

title: Spalling
description: Material that is breaking off structure. Typically found in concrete or masonry structures. Spalling can be caused by moisture and temperature problems.

title: Stud
description: One member of structural system used in building framing.

title: Abatement
description: Process of removing an item from area. Typically used to describe the process of removing asbestos from a building.

title: Asbestos
description: Fibrous material used as a fire resistant covering that has been determined to be a health risk. Anytime, building is being renovated and an area is opened up, asbestos must be removed or "abated” before work can start.

title: Fire Rating
description: Materials and structural systems are tested to determine how long they can withstand fire. Building codes mandate certain levels of fire ratings depending on materials used and building use. Fire rating is identified in hours of ability to withstand fire.

title: Fire Stop
description: Term describing solid filling set in all wall holes to stop fire from easily spreading from room to room.

title: Life Safety Inspection
description: Inspection of building to determine if safety equipment in building is functioning correctly.

title: OHSA
description: Occupational Safety & Health Administration- Government agency that defines safety protocol for worksites and workers.

title: "Red Tagged”
description: Represents item that didn’t pass inspection.

title: Temporary Occupancy
description: Inspection that gives owner the ability to inhabit structure with stipulations. If specific repairs are not completed by a date, the owner will not be allowed to continue using building.

title: 360 View of the Producer
description: A holistic producer profile that captures all available and significant information collected by a company about the producer,

title: 38a-1
description: Investment Company Act of 1940 and the Investment Advisers Act of 1940 Rule regarding Compliance Programs of Investment Companies and Investment Advisers.

title: 403(b) Notice
description: A form that is required to make 403(b) participants aware of the 20% federal tax penalty that may apply when making withdrawals from the plan.

title: 403(b) Plan
description: A type of tax-deferred retirement savings program available to employees of public schools, certain non-profits, and some members of the clergy.

title: 403(b) Withdrawal
description: Requires that the participants in a 403(b) plan are notified of the 20% federal tax penalty that may apply when making withdrawals from their 403(b).

title: 404(c)
description: The Employee Retirement Income Security Act (ERISA) Section 404(c) sets forth guidelines which all 401(k) plans must meet regarding educating employees about 401(k) plans and disclosure of plan and investment-related information to them.

title: 501(c)
description: The Internal Revenue Code under Section 501(c) describes various tax exempt organizations.

title: 501(c)(3)
description:
From a Finance perspective -  The Internal Revenue Code under Section 501(c) describes various tax-exempt organizations.


From a Deployment perspective - xyz

title: 5498 Form
description: An IRS filing that must be made by all employers who sponsor qualified plans. Reports deductible and nondeductible contributions, conversions, re-characterizations, and rollovers made within an Individual Retirement Account (IRA) during a given tax year.

title: 712 Form
description: An IRS form used to report the policy value upon the occurence of either change of ownership or death of the insured.

title: Abstraction
description: The act of masking or hiding essential characteristics and/or personally identifiable information.

title: Adoption Taxpayer Identification Number (ATIN)
description: A temporary identification number issued by the IRS to individuals who are in the process of legally adopting a U.S. citizen or resident but who cannot get a Social Security Number (SSN) for that child in time to file their tax return.

title: AFFIRM for Annuities
description: A third party annuity Order Entry Platform designed to integrate a carrier's complex product rules with a distributor's compliance processing

title: Affirmative Action
description: Any program, policy or procedure that an employer implements in order to correct past discrimination and prevent current and future discrimination within the workplace.

title: Agent's Authority
description: Lists the rules an agent must follow from the time a life application is completed until the time the policy is delivered.

title: Americans with Disabilities Act (ADA)
description: Civil rights law that prohibits discrimination against individuals with disabilities in all areas of public life, including jobs, schools, transportation, and all public and private places that are open to the general public and ensures the same rights an

title: Annual Statement
description: An annual report required to be filed with each state in which an insurer does business. This report provides a snapshot of the financial condition of a company and significant events which occurred throughout the reporting year.

title: Annual Statement Line of Business (ASLOB)
description: An accounting report grouped by industry-standard product categories.

title: Uniform Residential Loan Application Form (Fannie Mae/Freddie Mac 1003/FHA 2900/VA 1802) (URLA)
description: Form which is accepted by all major mortgage sources for application of residential mortgages.

title: VA automatic
description: Department of Veterans Affairs program which allows a lender to approve VA mortgage applications directly instead of sending the applications to the Department for approval.

title: VA FastTrack Refinance
description: Another term for a VA interest rate reduction refinance which is a VA to VA refinance accomplished solely to lower the interest rate.

title: VA Funding Fee
description: Fee charged on VA mortgages to cover the administrative costs of the program.

title: VA Loan
description: Mortgage loan made by an approved lender and guaranteed by the Department of Veterans Affairs. VA loans are made to eligible veterans and those currently serving in the military, and can have a lower down payment than other types of loans.

title: VA No-Bid
description: See NO-BID.

title: Appraisal Completion Certificate Comment Description
description: A free-form text field used to describe or comment on the Certification of Completion of property improvements that a property valuation was dependent upon.

title: Appraisal Completion Certificate Indicator
description: Indicates whether the appraisal report is a Certification of Completion of improvements upon which a previous appraisal report is dependent.

title: Automated Underwriting Evaluation Status Description
description: The status of the Automated Underwriting Certificate Request.

title: Building Permit Reference Identifier
description: The identifier used by the permitting authority to designate this instance of a permit. Often prefixed by the 2- or 4-digit year and an abbreviation of the type and/or work class of permit or certificate.

title: Certificate Application Date
description: The date of the certificate application as recorded by the local authority.

title: Certificate Authority Type Other Description
description: A free-form text field used to describe the status of a given certificate issued by a local authority if Other is selected as the Certificate Authority Type.

title: Certificate Expiration Date
description: The date of the certificate expiration as recorded by the local authority.

title: Certificate Issued Date
description: The date of the certificate issuance as recorded by the local authority.

title: Certificate Status Date
description: The date corresponding to the status of the certificate as indicated in the Certificate Status Type as assigned by the authority for this permit.

title: Certificate Status Type
description: The status for the certificate.

title: Certificate Status Type Other Description
description: A free-form text field used to describe the status of a given certificate issued by a local authority if Other is selected as the Certificate Status Type.

title: Certificate Type
description: The type of certificate issued by a local authority for the property.

title: Certificate Type Other Description
description: A free-form text field used to describe the certificate if Other is selected as the Certificate Type.

title: Credit Score FACTA Inquiries Indicator
description: This indicator is set to True when the Credit Risk Score Value of the borrower was negatively affected by the presence of credit inquiry records on their credit report. There may be FACT Act compliance requirements related to this alert message.

title: ENote Certified Indicator
description: Indicates whether the loan delivery data has been automatically certified against eNote data.

title: Fee Payment Allowable FHA Closing Cost Indicator
description: When true, indicates the fee is an allowable FHA Closing Cost.

title: FHA Alimony Liability Treatment Type
description: Identifies how the borrower or lender prefers that the judgment process treat alimony in an FHA transaction.

title: FHA Anniversary Date
description: Date the next premium change will be effective (YYYY-MM) for an FHA insured loan.

title: FHA Assignment Date
description: The date the lender registers the loan through FHA connection. (This date can impact the upfront and renewal MI rates for FHA Loans.)

title: FHA Automated Data Processing Identifier
description: The unique identifier for the Automated Data Processing (ADP) code used for Direct Endorsement (DE) processing of FHA loans.

title: FHA Borrower Certification Lead Paint Indicator
description: Property built prior to 1978, Lead Paint Notice provided to borrower. FHA Borrower Certification, HUD-92900-A (HUD/VA Addendum to URLA), section 25(6)

title: FHA Borrower Certification Own Four Or More Dwellings Indicator
description: Does borrower own four or more dwellings. FHA Borrower Certification, HUD-92900-A (HUD/VA Addendum to URLA), section 22f.

title: FHA Borrower Certification Own Other Property Indicator
description: Do you own or have you sold other real estate within the past 60 months on which there was a HUD/FHA mortgage? FHA Borrower Certification, HUD-92900-A, (HUD/VA Addendum to URLA) Section 22a:

title: FHA Borrower Certification Property Sold City Name
description: City of property sold in the past 60 months on which there was a HUD/FHA mortgage. FHA Borrower Certification, HUD-92900-A (HUD/VA Addendum to URLA), section 22d

title: FHA Borrower Certification Property Sold Postal Code
description: Postal Code of property sold in the past 60 months on which there was a HUD/FHA mortgage. FHA Borrower Certification, HUD-92900-A (HUD/VA Addendum to URLA), section 22d

title: FHA Borrower Certification Property Sold State Name
description: State of property sold in the past 60 months on which there was a HUD/FHA mortgage. FHA Borrower Certification, HUD-92900-A (HUD/VA Addendum to URLA), section 22d

title: FHA Borrower Certification Property Sold Street Address Line Text
description: Street address of property sold in the past 60 months on which there was a HUD/FHA mortgage. FHA Borrower Certification, HUD-92900-A (HUD/VA Addendum to URLA), section 22d

title: FHA Borrower Certification Property To Be Sold Indicator
description: If owned property within the past 60 months that was secured by a HUD/FHA mortgage, is it to be sold? FHA Borrower Certification, HUD-92900-A, (HUD/VA Addendum to URLA) Section 22a:

title: FHA Borrower Certification Rental Indicator
description: Property covered by mortgage is to be rented, or is adjacent to rental properties involving eight or more dwelling units in which the borrower has a financial interest. FHA Borrower Certification, HUD-92900-A (HUD/VA Addendum to URLA), section 22e

title: FHA Endorsement Date
description: The date of the FHA mortgage insurance certificate endorsement

title: FHA General Services Administration Identifier
description: The General Services Administrations (GSA) identifier from the List of Parties Excluded from Federal Procurement or Nonprocurement Programs on the FHA Mortgage Credit Analysis Worksheet document.

title: FHA Insurance Program Type
description: Type of FHA mortgage protection insurance program.

title: FHA Limited Denial Participation Identifier
description: Identifier obtained from review of HUDs Limited Denial of Participation (LDP) placed on the FHA Mortgage Credit Analysis Worksheet document.

title: FHA Loan Lender Identifier
description: An FHA-assigned identifier of the originator making an underwriting request using the FHA Total Scorecard program.

title: FHA Loan Sponsor Identifier
description: An FHA-assigned identifier of the lender acting as an approved sponsor for the originator making the underwriting request using the FHA Total Scorecard program.

title: FHA Non Owner Occupancy Rider Rule 248 Indicator
description: On the FHA Non Owner Occupancy Rider, this indicates that the Borrower is an Indian Tribe as provided in Section 248 of the National Housing Act or a serviceperson who is unable to occupy the Property because of his or her duty assignment as provided in Section 216 or Subsection(b)(4) or (f) of Section 222 of the National Housing Act.

title: FHA Pending Premium Change Date
description: Effective date of pending premium amount for an FHA insured loan.

title: FHA Pre Review Results Value
description: The credit risk decision issued by the FHA TOTAL Mortgage Scorecard based solely on the algorithm score. (Does not take into account review rules or credit overrides.)

title: FHA Refinance Original Existing FHA Case Identifier
description: Original FHA Case Number for refinance

title: FHA Secondary Residence Indicator
description: When true, indicates that the property usage falls under the FHA Secondary Residence policy and guidelines.

title: FHA Underwriter Computerized Homes Underwriting System Identifier
description: The FHA assigned number that identifies the Direct Endorsement underwriter authorized to approve the loan on behalf of the FHA. (Frequently referred to as the CHUMS ID.)

title: FHA VA Borrower Certification Sales Price Exceeds Appraised Value Type
description: FHA/VA Borrower acknowledgement when Sales Price exceeds the Appraised Value. FHA/VA Borrower Certification, HUD-92900-A (HUD/VA Addendum to URLA), section 25(3)

title: Flood Certification Identifier
description: The certification number assigned by the compliance company when an order is received from the submitting / requesting party.

title: Flood Determination Life of Loan Indicator
description: Indicates if the flood contract with the compliance company is for the Life of the Loan.

title: Flood Product Certify Date
description: The date on which the flood determination was assessed by the certification provider.

title: GFE Loan Originator Fee Payment Credit Type
description: Identifies the type of application of loan originator credit(s) to be reflected on the GFE and the HUD1.

title: Green Certification Association Name
description: The name of the association or program providing the Green certification such as National Association of Homebuilders or LEED.

title: Green Certification Level Awarded Date
description: The date the Green program certification was obtained for this property.

title: Green Certification Level Name
description: The level or rating from the indicated Green program that was certified for this property.

title: Home Buyers Homeownership Education Certificate Indicator
description: Indicates whether the Home Buyers/Home Ownership Education certificate is included in the loan file.

title: Housing Counseling Certification Issued Date
description: The date the housing counseling certificate of completion was issued.

title: HUD 235 Subsidy Payment Effective Date
description: The effective date of the HUD 235 Subsidy Amount that is being reported.

title: HUD Adequate Available Assets Indicator
description: Indicates that borrower has adequate available assets for HUD approval

title: HUD Adequate Effective Income Indicator
description: Indicates borrower effective income is adequate for HUD approval

title: HUD Counseling Initiated Indicator
description: When true, indicates that the borrower has agreed to HUD counseling as a condition of the loan modification.

title: HUD Credit Characteristics Indicator
description: Indicates borrower meets credit characteristics for HUD approval

title: HUD Stable Effective Income Indicator
description: Indicates borrower's stable effective income meets HUD approval

title: HUD1 Cash To Or From Borrower Indicator
description: When True, indicates that cash is due to the Borrower. When False, indicates that cash is due from the borrower. This field is for use as required on the HUD-1.

title: HUD1 Cash To Or From Seller Indicator
description: When True, indicates that cash is due to the Seller. When False, indicates that cash is due from the Seller. This field is for use as required on the HUD-1.

title: HUD1 Conventional Insured Indicator
description: When True, this field is used to indicate, as required on the HUD-1, that the loan transaction is a conventional loan with Mortgage Insurance required.

title: HUD1 Line Item Additional Text Description
description: A free-form text field used to provide a supplemental comment or remark to an individual HUD1 Line Item. This text is in addition to the HUD1 Line Item Description.

title: HUD1 Line Item Description
description: The description of the specified HUD-1 line item.

title: HUD1 Line Item From Date
description: Items that require adjustments for a time period require the listing of the period in which they were paid. This is the start date of the payment adjustment as reflected on the description line on the HUD-1.

title: HUD1 Line Item Paid By Type
description: The party responsible for payment of the specified HUD-1 line item.

title: HUD1 Line Item To Date
description: Items that require adjustments for a time period require the listing of the period in which they were paid. This is the end date of the payment adjustment as reflected on the description line on the HUD-1.

title: HUD1 Settlement Date
description: A placeholder for the date specified as the Settlement Date on the HUD-1. This field contains the one date of multiple dates associated with the loan transaction (e.g., Disbursement Date, Closing Date, Recording Date) that is identified as the Settlement Date as required on the HUD-1.

title: Issue Regulation Related Indicator
description: When true, indicates that an issue is associated with a government regulation compliance concern.

title: Lead Based Paint Certification Required Indicator
description: Indicates that a Lead Base Certification is a requirement of closing.

title: License Identifier
description: The identifier of the license or certificate issued to the party. The attribute IdentifierOwnerURI identifies the issuer of the license or certificate.

title: License Issuing Authority State Code
description: The two-character representation of the US state, US Territory, Canadian Province, Military APO FPO, or Territory in which the party is licensed or certified to operate.

title: License Issuing Authority State Name
description: The name of the state in which the party is licensed or certified to operate.

title: Manufactured Home HUD Certification Label Identifier
description: An identifier made up of 3 letters followed by 6 numbers (in some cases 7 numbers). It may be found on a (red) metal label affixed to the exterior of the manufactured home. It might read something like ULI 012345. As per HUD regulations, the label identifier consists of a 3 letter designation which identifies the production inspection primary inspection agency, and which the Sectary shall assign. Each label shall be marked with a 6 digit number which the label supplier shall furnish. The labels shall be stamped with numbers sequentially.

title: Manufactured Home HUD Data Plate Attached Indicator
description: Indicates that the manufactured home has a HUD data plate attached.

title: Manufactured Home HUD Data Plate Data Source Description
description: A free-form text field describing the source of information about the HUD data plate if it is not attached to the manufactured home.

title: Manufactured Home HUD Data Plate Identifier
description: An identifier that is assigned by the manufacturer to an individual manufactured home unit. It may be found on the HUD Data Plate, which is affixed to the interior of the manufactured home.

title: Manufactured Home Installed Date
description: Reports the date a Certificate of Occupancy or its equivalent was issued for the development of a lot and placement of a manufactured home on a permanent foundation.

title: Manufactured Home Meets HUD Requirements For Location Description
description: A free-form text field describing how the manufactured home meets meet the HUD Wind Road Load and Thermal Zone requirements for its location.

title: Manufactured Home Meets HUD Requirements for Location Indicator
description: Indicates that the manufactured home meets meet the HUD Wind Road Load and Thermal Zone requirements for its location.

title: MI Certificate Expiration Date
description: The expiration date of the Commitment/Certificate issued by the MI.

title: MI Certificate Type
description: Specifies the type of mortgage insurance certificate required by the customer.

title: MI Certification Status Type
description: Defines the party that will obtain an MI Certificate.

title: MI Certification Status Type Other Description
description: A free-form text field used to collect additional information when Other is selected for MI Certification Status Type.

title: Optional Product Provider Account Identifier
description: An account identifier used by the product provider to identify this account in its own systems. For an optional insurance plan this would be the insurance plan certificate numbers assigned by the insurance company

title: Original Flood Determination Loan Identifier
description: The loan number assigned to the original flood determination order. Used for identifying a loan that has been previously certified (e.g., refinance, second, servicing transfer, etc.)

title: Other Party Paid FHA VA Closing Costs Amount
description: The estimated closing costs which will be paid by a party, other than the borrower or seller, on the subject property. Used for FHA or VA loans.

title: Other Party Paid FHA VA Closing Costs Percent
description: The percentage of estimated closing costs that will be paid by any party other than the borrower or seller including any seller paid prepaids but excluding discount points.

title: Previous VA Home Loan Indicator
description: When true, indicates the borrower has previously had a VA home loan.

title: Property Valuation Service Type
description: Provides a categorization for valuation products in terms of USPAP compliance and level of professional services required.

title: Regulatory Agency Lender Identifier
description: Identification of the lender funding the loan. The identification is as follows: FDIC-insured lenders indicate their FDIC Insurance Certificate Number; Federally-insured credit unions indicate their charter/insurance number; Farm Credit institutions indicate their UNINUM number. Other lenders who fund loans sold to or securitized by FNMA or FHLMC enter FNMA or FHLMC seller/servicer number.

title: Section Classification Type
description: The section number on the Good Faith Estimate/HUD-1 associated with a fee type.

title: SFDMS Automated Default Processing Identifier
description: Identifies the insuring section and the applicable HUD insurance fund; identifies an assistance payment contract; identifies where the lender has the option under its contract of mortgage ins to receive benefits in default. (Reference HUD SFDMS Guide)

title: Site Zoning Compliance Type
description: Indicates the level of compliance of the subject Site to zoning regulations.

title: Sold Under HUD Single Family Property Disposition Program Indicator
description: On the FHA Non Owner Occupancy Rider, this indicates that the Security Instrument applies to Property sold under HUD Single Family Property Disposition Program and meets the requirements thereof.

title: Spousal VA Benefits Eligibility Indicator
description: When true, indicates that the individual is a surviving spouse of a Veteran who served and was Missing In Action (MIA) /Killed In Action (KIA), a Veteran who died of a condition or impairment connected to his/her service in the Armed Forces (as determined by VA or DoD), or a Veteran whose service connected disability/impairment, they believe, entitles them to benefits from the VA.

title: SSN Certification Indicator
description: When true, indicates that the Social Security Number has been certified.

title: Transcript Certified Copy Indicator
description: When true, indicates that the user requested a certified copy for court or administrative proceeding. Used on the IRS Form 4506.

title: VA Appraisal Type
description: Specifies the property appraisal type used, as appears on VA Loan Summary Sheet (VA 26-0286), for example.

title: VA Appraisal Type Other Description
description: A free-form text field which contains the description of the type of VA appraisal when Other is selected as the VA Appraisal Type.

title: VA Benefit Related Indebtedness Indicator
description: When true, indicates the borrower has a VA benefit-related indebtedness as defined by the VA for purposes of VA Form 26-8937 - Verification of VA Benefits.

title: VA Borrower Certification Occupancy Type
description: VA Borrower Certification type of occupancy. VA Borrower Certification, HUD-92900-A (HUD/VA Addendum to URLA), section 25(2)

title: VA Borrower Co Borrower Married Indicator
description: Indicates whether the co-borrower is married to the borrower. Used for VA loans only.

title: VA Borrower Surviving Spouse Indicator
description: VA Borrower Surviving Spouse Indicator

title: VA Claim Folder Identifier
description: A unique alpahnumeric string identifying the number associated with the VA claim folder as assigned by the VA.

title: VA Disability Benefit Claim Indicator
description: When true, indicates the borrower has filed a claim for VA disability benefits prior to discharge from active duty service.

title: VA Eligibility Indicator
description: When true, indicates that this instance of military service is used to determine VA eligibility. NOTE: Only one instance of this container/element should have this set to true.

title: VA Entitlement Identifier
description: VA entitlement identifier from Certificate of Eligibility for VA Loan Summary Sheet.

title: VA Funding Fee Exemption Type
description: The Exemption Status given by the VA Administration (exemption from VA Funding Fees).

title: VA Funding Fee Exemption Type Other Description
description: A free-form text field used to collect additional information when Other is selected for VA Funding Fee Exemption Type.

title: VA Loan Guaranty Certificate Effective Date
description: The date that the current VA guaranty certificate was issued for the originated loan.

title: VA Loan Procedure Type
description: Specifies the procedure used to qualify the borrower(s).

title: VA Loan Procedure Type Other Description
description: A free-form text field which contains the description of the type of VA loan procedure when Other is selected as the VA Loan Procedure Type.

title: VA Loan Program Type
description: Identifies the type of VA Loan Program established by Title 38 of the US Code.

title: VA Loan Program Type Other Description
description: A free-form text field used to describe the VA Loan Program Type if Other is selected as the VA Loan Program Type.

title: VA Loan Termination Date
description: The date the VA loan was terminated.

title: VA Loan Termination Type
description: The value from a MISMO prescribed list that identifies the reason the VA loan was terminated.

title: VA Loan Termination Type Other Description
description: A free-form text field used to collect additional information when Other is selected for VA Loan Termination Type.

title: VA Primary Obligor Indicator
description: When true, indicates that the borrower's VA entitlement was used to originate the loan and this borrower is considered the primary VA obligor.

title: VA Reasonable Value Improvements Completion Indicator
description: When true, indicates that any improvements upon which the reasonable value of the property is predicated and which were not approved subsequent to completion by a compliance inspector designated by the Secretary have been completed properly.

title: VA Substitution Of Entitlement Indicator
description: When true, indicates that a borrower's VA entitlement has been exchanged for another borrower's VA entitlement.

title: VA Title Vesting Type
description: The VA specific vesting under which the property is, or will be, held.

title: VA Title Vesting Type Other Description
description: A free-form text field which contains the description of the type of VA title vesting when Other is selected as the VA Title Vesting Type.

title: Veteran Status Indicator
description: When true, indicates the borrower qualifies as a Veteran under HUD guidelines and that the loan application should be evaluated as a 203(b)(2) Veteran Loan. If any borrower qualifies as a Veteran under VA guidelines then the loan (including all borrowers)

title: 203K Borrower Acknowledgment
description:
Borrower acknowledgement that they will conform with the requirements laid out by HUD for a 203(k) Rehabilitation Loan.
