title: 203K Borrower Identity Of Interest Certification
description: Certification that the borrower does not have an identity-of-interest with the seller of the property and does not have a conflict of interest with any other party to the transaction, including the realtor, lender, contractor, consultant, and/or the appraiser. In addition, certifying that the borrower is not obtaining any source of funds or acting as a 'strawbuyer' for another individual, partnership, company, or investment club.

title: 203K Consultant Identity Of Interest Statement
description: Certification letter completed by all consultants and plan reviewers who are required to sign the following certification after preparing/reviewing the work write-up and cost estimate. The signer certifies that all items requiring correction and that the rehabilitation proposal now meets all HUD requirements for 203(k) Rehabilitation Mortgage Insurance.

title: 203K Draw Request
description:
Provides information required to release funds based on work in place. Must be signed by contractor, borrower and inspector. Form HUD-9746-A



203k HUD

title: Appraisal Review - Exterior Only Inspection With Value Opinion
description: A USPAP compliant review by an appraiser in which the scope of work includes the development of a value conclusion and an exterior-only inspection of the subject property was performed in the field.

title: Appraisal Review - Exterior Only Without Value Opinion
description: A USPAP compliant review by an appraiser in which the scope of work DOES NOT include the development of a value conclusion and an exterior-only inspection of the subject property was performed in the field.

title: Appraisal Review - Interior Exterior Inspection With Value Opinion
description: A USPAP compliant review by an appraiser in which the scope of work includes the development of a value conclusion and an interior and exterior inspection of the subject property was performed in the field.

title: Appraisal Review - Interior Exterior Without Value Opinion
description: A USPAP compliant review by an appraiser in which the scope of work DOES NOT include the development of a value conclusion and an interior and exterior inspection of the subject property was performed in the field.

title: Appraisal Review - No Inspection With Value Opinion
description: A USPAP compliant review by an appraiser in which the scope of work includes the development of a value conclusion however no inspection of the subject property was performed.

title: Appraisal Review - Without Value Opinion
description: A USPAP compliant review by an appraiser in which the scope of work DOES NOT include the development of a value conclusion and no inspection of the subject property was performed.

title: Assurance Of Completion
description: Describes escrowed repairs and certifies that escrowed repairs will be completed. Provided by Lender.

title: Elevation Certificate
description: Certifies elevation information necessary to ensure compliance with community floodplain management ordinances, to determine the proper insurance premium rate, and to support a request for a Letter of Map Amendment (LOMA) or Letter of Map Revision based on fill (LOMR-F).

title: FHA MI Premium Netting Authorization
description: Determines the appropriate amount for an FHA streamlined refinance loan.

title: FHA Five Day Waiver
description: Confirms that the borrower waives the requirement to receive the Notice to Homebuyer five days before closing.

title: FHA Limited Denial Of Participation General Services Administration Checklist
description: Confirms that a borrower is not recorded on the LDP/GSA (Limited Denial of Participation/General Services Administration) lists, and therefore is eligible for an FHA loan.

title: FHA Mortgage Credit Analysis Worksheet
description: Determines the appropriate amount for an FHA loan.

title: FHA Referral Checklist
description: Confirms that all requirements have been met prior to FHA foreclosure. Provided to FHA.

title: FHA Refinance Maximum Mortgage Worksheet
description: Determines loan amount for refinance loan, included with or attached to the MCAW. Required by HUD, provided by Underwriter.

title: FHA Refinance Of Borrowers In Negative Equity Positions Borrower Certification
description: Borrower's certification that they have not been convicted within the last ten (10) years of felony larceny, theft, fraud, forgery, money laundering, or tax evasion. (HUD Form 92918)

title: General Loan Acknowledgment
description: Confirms receipt of all the disclosures in the Disclosure Booklet, HUD Guide to Settlement Costs. Also used to document the float/lock rate requests and mortgage insurance requests and provide the Appraisal Notice to the borrower.

title: IRS W9
description: Provides the borrowers tax identification number and certifies truthfulness of data provided. Provided by borrower via IRS W9 form.

title: Mortgagees Certification And Application For Assistance Or Interest Reduction Payments
description: Mortgagee's Certification and Application for Assistance or Interest Reduction Payments due under HUD Sections 235(b), 235(j), or 235(i). HUD-93102 (04/2003).

title: Proof Of HUD Waiver CAIVRS Clearance
description: Indicates the review and approval of decision for waiver or resolution of CAIVRS clearance from a HUD representative.

title: Proof Of Tax Deferral Or Exemption
description: Evidence from state or local authority of tax deferral or exemption. An example is a Homestead Exemption Certificate.

title: Request For Copy Of Tax Return
description: Authorizes taxing authority (such as IRS) to provide certified copy of borrowers tax return

title: Settlement Statement - HUD1
description: Settlement Statement (HUD-1)

title: Settlement Statement - HUD1A
description: Settlement Statement (HUD-1A) - Optional Form for Transactions without Sellers.

title: VA Acknowledgment Of No Inspection
description: Acknowledges the borrower's awareness that the property was not inspected and will not qualify for government assistance in the correction of structural defects.

title: VA Certificate Of Eligibility
description: Confirms a person's veteran status and prior home loan usage.

title: VA Certificate Of Reasonable Value
description: Confirms the maximum value and loan amount for a VA mortgage.

title: VA Collection Policy Notice
description: Informs the borrower of the actions that can be taken by the VA if a borrower defaults on a loan.

title: VA Foreclosure Bid Letter
description: Describes the procedure for purchasing a foreclosed VA property.

title: VA Funding Fee Notice
description: Informs the borrower of VA funding fee costs.

title: VA Interest Rate Reduction Refinancing Loan Worksheet
description: Determines amount current VA homeowners can reduce their interest rate with no out of pocket expenses and minimal documentation.

title: VA Loan Analysis
description: Determines whether a veteran qualifies for a VA loan and whether a lenders adheres to VA standards.

title: VA Loan Summary Sheet
description: VA Form 26-0286. Describes key information utilized in the comprehensive risk assessment of the Veterans's mortgage application, and the final underwriting decision. This is similar but is not the Underwriting Transmittal.

title: VA Rate Reduction Refinance Information And Agreement
description: Acknowledges the borrower is aware of the terms of the existing loan and the terms of the new loan, whether the payment will be increasing or decreasing and how long it takes to recoup all closing costs.

title: VA Report And Certification Of Loan Disbursement
description: Describes details of a VA closed loan.

title: VA Request For Certification Of Eligibility For Home Loan Benefit
description: Provides VA with information to make determination of a borrower's VA eligibility.

title: VA Verification Of Benefit Related Indebtedness
description: Confirms whether a veteran has the ability to incur debt on a loan.

title: Order Compliance/Fraud Test
description: Process of requesting analysis and testing for regulatory compliance and fraud prevention.

title: Review Tax Certification
description: Process of reviewing the real estate tax certification, as provided by the Settlement Agent and/or Title Agent, to confirm taxes required to be collected during the loan closing.

title: Determine VA Eligibility
description: Process in which the Lender determines whether a Borrower is eligible for a VA mortgage.

title: Establish Forced Escrow
description: The process of converting a non-escrowed loan into an escrowed account due to non-payment of taxes or insurance or non-compliance with the note.

title: Maintain Evidence of Compliance
description: The process of creating, maintaining documentation evidencing the servicer's response to a qualified written request (QWR) from a consumer. The QWR is a request for action or information as outlined in the National Servicing Rules and supplemental guidance from the CFPB or other regulator(s). Per the National Servicing Rules, a servicer must be able to communicate their compliance actions to regulators, transferees or interested third parties when requested.

title: Manage High Touch Loans
description: The process of assigning and managing loans made under alternative loan programs and products such as state bond programs, ARMs, HELOCs, Buydowns or loans made to an acknowledged VIP. Includes compliance with Servicemember's Civil Relief Act (SCRA).

title: Perform Regulatory Compliance
description: The process of assuring compliance to the servicing rules as published by regulatory agencies. This includes required notices, handling of consumer complaints and tracking of activities.

title: Certificate Authority or Issuing Authority
description: A trusted third-party organization or company that issues, manages, renews, and revokes Digital Certificates used to create Digital Signatures. The Certificate Authority registers the certificate holder’s name and address and allows others to see if the certificate is valid, revoked, or expired. The third-party certificate authority also has the ability to confirm the identity of the certificate holder. This term is also defined in the MERS® eRegistry Procedures Manual available at members.mersinc.org.

title: authority approvals
description: The necessary sign-off by council, fire department, government, etc., confirming design compliance with laws to enable a facility to be constructed or a transaction to be completed.

title: Dangerous Goods Packing Certificate
description: A document attached to the dangerous goods declaration wherein the responsible party declares that the cargo has been stowed in compliance with IMDG regulations and is properly secured.

title: 20% Mandatory Withholding
description: In a distribution of assets to participants from qualified 401(a)(k) plans and 403(b) plans, the IRS requires the relinquishing organization to withhold 20% of the taxable funds (except in the case of Hardship withdrawals) from the distribution.

title: Allocations Model
description: Set of rules and processes for transferring dollars and/or assigning dimensionality that dictate how the financial activity is distributed.

title: Allowables
description: How much we are allowed to spend to drive sales that will still give us a positive return on investment.

title: Allowance
description: When making withholding elections on a W-4, this allows users to choose to edit how much federal tax is withheld. The more allowances, the less money withheld. NOTE: This does not determine your tax liability, i.e. how much you owe; it only determines h

title: Allowed Amount
description: Maximum amount on which payment is based for covered health care services. If a provider charges more than the allowed amount, the subscriber may have to pay the difference.

title: American National Standards Institute(ANSI)
description: An industry group that focuses upon establishing industry-wide standards for a variety of purposes and disciplines. It is a member of ISO (Industry Standards Organization).

title: Amortization
description: Gradual balance reductions. Normally, the reduction is made according to a predetermined schedule. Items eligible for amortization include prepaid assets, VOBA, and intangible assets such as trade names, renewal rights, patents, copyrights, etc.

title: Amortized Cost
description: Amortized cost is that accumulated portion of the recorded cost of a fixed asset that has been charged to expense through either depreciation or amortization. Depreciation is used to ratably reduce the cost of a tangible fixed asset, and amortization is u

title: Amortized Value
description: The value of a fixed asset as determined by the process of amortization. Generally this is the cost of the fixed asset adjusted for amortization of any discount or premium.

title: Anniversary Begin Balance Amount
description: The dollar amount balance on the last policy anniversary.

title: Anniversary Discount
description: A type of discount applied to an insurance policy based upon the number of years the policyholder has had continuous coverage with the current insurer.

title: Walking Money
description: Funds borrowed in excess of costs required to develop and build a real estate project.

title: Adjustment Change Occurrence Type
description: Indicates the reason for the Interest Rate, principal and interest Payment or Service Fee change on an existing mortgage loan.

title: Appraiser Additional File Identifier
description: Secondary report identifier used by the appraiser to identify appraisal reports. This field may carry the FHA number, case number, loan number or some other identifier.

title: Automated Underwriting System Type
description: A value from a MISMO prescribed list that represents the automated underwriting system used to evaluate a loan.

title: Bid Open Amount
description: The initial opening bid amount presented at the foreclosure sale for a property.

title: Buydown Total Subsidy Amount
description: The total dollar amount of funds held for the buydown subsidy portion of the monthly principal and interest payment, to be discharged according to the buydown schedule.

title: Combined LTV Ratio Considered In Decision Indicator
description: When true, indicates that the combined LTV ratio was used in the risk assessment or approval decision for a loan application.

title: Contact Point Email Value
description: The email address for the contact.

title: Credit Comment Expiration Date
description: Date the comment expires

title: Credit Public Record Court Name
description: The name of the court reporting the public record.

title: Credit Public Record Defendant Name
description: The name of the defendant in a public record.

title: Credit Public Record Derogatory Data Indicator
description: This element indicates whether or not the public record contains adverse or derogatory information.

title: Credit Public Record Disposition Date
description: This element provides the date that the Public Record Disposition Type first became effective.

title: Credit Public Record Disposition Type
description: This is the enumerated disposition or the public record as of the Disposition Date. If the disposition does not fit one of the enumerated categories, select Other, and enter it in the Credit Public Record Disposition Type Other Description element.

title: Credit Public Record Disposition Type Other Description
description: If the Credit Public Record Disposition Type is set to Other, enter the disposition in this element.

title: Credit Public Record Docket Identifier
description: The Docket Identifier can be a Case Number, Docket Number, Public Record Book, Page or Sequence Number.

title: Credit Public Record Filed Date
description: The date that the public record was filed by the court.

title: Credit Public Record Legal Obligation Amount
description: This is the amount listed in the public record that the defendant is obligated to pay.

title: Credit Public Record Manual Update Indicator
description: This element indicates whether or not the data in the public record has been manually updated by the credit bureau based on an investigation.

title: Credit Public Record Paid Date
description: The date that the Legal Obligation Amount was paid to zero.

title: Credit Public Record Payment Frequency Type
description: This element indicates the frequency of payments allowed for the Legal Obligation Amount.

title: Credit Public Record Payment Frequency Type Other Description
description: A free-form text field used to collect additional information when Other is selected for Credit Public Record Payment Frequency Type.

title: Credit Public Record Plaintiff Name
description: The name of the plaintiff in a public record.

title: Credit Public Record Reported Date
description: The date that the public record data was last reported by the court to the credit repository bureau.

title: Credit Public Record Settled Date
description: The date that the public record case was settled.

title: Credit Public Record Type
description: This is the enumerated type of public record reported by the credit bureau. If the type does not fit one of the enumerated categories, enter the type in the Credit Public Record Type Other Description element.

title: Credit Public Record Type Other Description
description: If the Public Record Type is set to Other, enter the type in this element.

title: Credit Rating Code Type
description: Identifies which system of Manner Of Payment (MOP) rating codes is in the credit report. If Other is selected, then the name of the coding system will appear in the Credit Rating Code Type Other Description.

title: Credit Rating Code Type Other Description
description: If the Credit Rating Code Type is set to Other, enter its description in this data attribute.

title: Credit Reference Type
description: Specifies the type of credit history or type of payments used as credit history to establish acceptable credit reputation.

title: Credit Reference Type Other Description
description: A free-form text field used to capture the Credit Reference Type if Other is selected.

title: Credit Report Authorization Indicator
description: Indicates that the borrower gave the lender consent to pull credit report.

title: Credit Report First Issued Date
description: Date and time the referenced credit report was first issued.

title: Credit Report Identifier
description: A reference number assigned by the credit bureau to a specific credit report. This report number is also referenced when a Reissue, Upgrade, or Status Query of an existing report is requested.

title: Credit Report Last Updated Date
description: The date and time that the referenced credit report was last updated or revised.

title: Credit Report Merge Type
description: This element indicates how duplicate data from multiple sources is handled on a credit report.

title: Credit Report Price Amount
description: The price of the credit report produced on the borrower(s).

title: Credit Report Price Type
description: This describes the type of the Credit Report Price (Net, Tax, Total or Other). If Other is selected enter the description into the Credit Report Price Type Other Description element.

title: Credit Report Price Type Other Description
description: When Other is specified in Price Type, this element contains its description.

title: Credit Report Product Description
description: This is additional information that more completely describes the credit report product being requested.

title: Credit Report Request Action Type
description: Select the type of service action being requested. If the service action refers to an existing report, specify which one in the Credit Report Identifier.

title: Credit Report Request Action Type Other Description
description: This describes the desired request action when the Credit Report Request Action Type is set to Other.

title: Credit Report Transaction Identifier
description: Uniquely identifies a specific instance of a credit report transaction.

title: Credit Report Type
description: The type of credit report that was requested or produced. Most common types are Merged report (data from credit data repositories is merged), and RMCR (Residential Mortgage Credit Report - contains verified liabilities, employment, etc.)

title: Credit Report Type Other Description
description: When Credit Report Type is set to Other, enter its description in this element.

title: Credit Repositories Selected Count
description: This element stores the number of repository bureaus desired for a credit request. When a requestor uses this element, they are selecting the number of repositories to be pulled, not specific bureaus. The credit bureau would then choose which bureaus to be pulled based on a methodology agreed on with their customer (for example, zip code or customer preference).

title: Credit Repository Included Equifax Indicator
description: This element indicates whether Equifax is included in either the request or response.

title: Credit Repository Included Experian Indicator
description: This element indicates whether Experian is included in either the request or response.

title: Credit Repository Included Other Repository Name
description: This element indicates whether another repository source is included in either the request or response.

title: Credit Repository Included Trans Union Indicator
description: This element indicates whether Trans Union is included in either the request or response.

title: Credit Repository Single Source Indicator
description: If true, indicates the credit report was based on the input from a single credit repository. Also known as a single in-file credit report.

title: Credit Repository Source Indicator
description: Indicates whether a Credit Repository Source is available. If a Credit Repository Source is available then the source can be provided in Credit Repository Source Type.

title: Credit Repository Source Type
description: This element describes the source of the credit file, Equifax, Experian, Trans Union or Unspecified if the specific sources are not specified.

title: Credit Repository Source Type Other Description
description: When Credit Repository Source Type is set to Other, enter its value in this data element.

title: Credit Repository Subscriber Code
description: This is the subscriber code (sometimes called member code) of the liability holder or provider of data to the credit repository bureau.

title: Credit Request Datetime
description: A system generated date and time stamp enclosed within each request to identify the initiation time of the credit request.

title: Credit Request Type
description: The Credit Request Type specifies either an Individual Report on one person, or a Joint Report on two married persons.

title: Credit Response Alert Message Adverse Indicator
description: This indicator is set to Y when the Credit Response Alert Message contains information which may be considered adverse and may require further investigation or other action.

title: Credit Response Alert Message Category Type
description: Describes the general category of the alert message. This allows for automated processing by systems reading the credit alert messages.

title: Credit Response Alert Message Category Type Other Description
description: When Credit Response Alert Message Category Type is set to Other, enter its value in this data element.

title: Credit Response Alert Message Code
description: This is the code value associated with the Credit Response Alert Message Text and/or Credit Response Alert Message Type.

title: Credit Response Alert Message Code Source Type
description: This element identifies the name of the source for the code values used in the Credit Response Alert Message Code. The enumeration definition identifies the source document and name of the table that contains the code values.

title: Credit Response Alert Message Code Source Type Other Description
description: When the Credit Response Alert Message Code Source Type has a value of Other, this element identifies the name of the source for the code values used in the Credit Response Alert Message Code.

title: Credit Response Alert Message Text
description: Text of the alert message.

title: Credit Response Alert Message Type
description: Lists the name of the repository bureau service or other service that generated the alert message.

title: Credit Response Alert Message Type Other Description
description: When Credit Response Alert Message Type is set to Other, enter its value in this data element.

title: Credit Score Category Type
description: An enumerated list that describes the general type or purpose of a credit score model. This allows LOS systems to extract scores by a more general category, without having to know the specific score model names.

title: Credit Score Category Type Other Description
description: When Credit Score Category Type is set to ""Other"", enter its value in this data element.

title: Credit Score Category Version Type
description: A value from a MISMO prescribed list that represents a specific version, release of a Credit Score Category Type.

title: Credit Score Category Version Type Other Description
description: A free-form text field that specifies the enumeration when the value of Other is used for Credit Score Category Version Type.

title: Credit Score Considered In Decision Indicator
description: When true, indicates that a credit score was used in the risk assessment or approval decision for a loan application.

title: Credit Score Date
description: Date that the referenced credit score was produced.

title: Credit Score Exclusion Reason Type
description: An enumerated list of reasons why a credit score could not be generated.

title: Credit Score FACTA Inquiries Indicator
description: This indicator is set to True when the Credit Risk Score Value of the borrower was negatively affected by the presence of credit inquiry records on their credit report. There may be FACT Act compliance requirements related to this alert message.

title: Credit Score Factor Code
description: Factors of the borrower's credit which give context to the referenced credit score. The factor is normally a numeric code. The Credit Score Factor Text contains the text for the factor code.

title: Credit Score Factor Text
description: The text remarks associated with a Credit Score Factor

title: Credit Score Histogram Interval High Value
description: The highest possible value for the score model within the given credit score histogram interval.

title: Credit Score Histogram Interval Low Value
description: The lowest possible value for the score model within the given credit score histogram interval.

title: Credit Score Histogram Interval Score Range Occurrence Percent
description: The percent of consumers that have score values within this credit score histogram interval.

title: Credit Score Impairment Type
description: Identifies a characteristic of the Credit Score that impairs its effectiveness as an indicator of credit risk.

title: Credit Score Impairment Type Other Description
description: A free-form text field used to collect additional information when Other is selected for Credit Score Impairment Type.

title: Credit Score Maximum Value
description: This is the upper range of possible score values for this Credit Score Model Name Type. The range of credit score values is required to be part of the FACTA disclosure.

title: Credit Score Minimum Value
description: This is the lower range of possible score values for this Credit Score Model Name Type. The range of credit score values is required to be part of the FACTA disclosure.

title: Credit Score Model Name Type
description: A value from a MISMO prescribed list that specifies the score algorithm model name used to produce the referenced credit risk score.

title: Credit Score Model Name Type Other Description
description: When the Credit Score Model Name Type is set to Other, this element holds the description.

title: Credit Score Model Range of Scores Description
description: The range of scores possible under the credit score model.

title: Credit Score Provider Name
description: Identifies the name of the company providing the credit score data. This is one of the requirements of the 2003 FACT Act.

title: Credit Score Provider URL
description: Specifies the URL or web site address of the company providing the credit score data.

title: Credit Score Rank Percentile Description
description: A detailed description of how the credit score compares to the scores of other consumers.

title: Credit Score Rank Percentile Value
description: The percentile that the parties credit score is in comparison to all consumers.

title: Credit Score Value
description: Numeric credit score resulting from credit evaluation model.

title: Credit Summary Data Set Name
description: The Credit Summary Data Set Name-Value pair data provides a standard method of providing a set of summary data. The Data Set Name identifies the type of summary data. The Data Set Value contains the actual data described by the Data Set Name.

title: Credit Summary Data Set Value
description: This element holds the actual data value described by the Credit Summary Data Set Name attribute.

title: Credit Summary Name
description: This is the name used to label or describe an individual group of summary data elements. It is useful when there are multiple groups of summary data elements within a credit report.

title: Credit Summary Text
description: Any type of additional summary data that is provided by the credit bureau.

title: Credit Union Indicator
description: When true, indicates that the lender is a Credit Union.

title: Creditor Servicing Of Loan Statement Type
description: Specifies the certainty of the originating lender's or creditor's intention to service the mortgage loan.

title: Creditor Servicing Of Loan Statement Type Other Description
description: A free-form text field used to capture additional information when Other is selected for Creditor Servicing Of Loan Statement Type.

title: Cumulative Advance Amount
description: The dollar amount of the cumulative total advances made by a servicer for a specified Advance Type.

title: Cumulative Days On Market Count
description: The total number of days a property is on the market unsold - inclusive of all listing status change dates, from the original listing date to time the listing is selected for the valuation report.

title: Current Accrued Interest Amount
description: The dollar amount of interest accrued on the loan between the last paid installment date and the date reported.

title: Current Advance Amount
description: The total dollar amount advanced by the servicer for a specified Advance Type for the current reporting period.

title: Current Advance Reimbursement Amount
description: The portion of the payment allocated to repayment of deferred expenses due to the investor.

title: Current Advance Repayment Amount
description: The total dollar amount applied to repay funds advanced by the servicer for a specified Advance Type for the current reporting period.

title: Current Buydown Subsidy Amount Total Amount
description: Provides an arithmetic total of the Current Buydown Subsidy Amount data items within the Loan container in this data set where Payment State Type equals Current.

title: Current First Mortgage Holder Type
description: Specifies the investor holding the first mortgage that is being refinanced.

title: Current First Mortgage Holder Type Other Description
description: A free-form text field used to collect additional information when Other is selected for Current First Mortgage Holder Type.

title: Current HELOC Maximum Balance Amount
description: The total dollar amount of the line of credit as of the date reported.

title: Current Income Monthly Total Amount
description: The monthly total amount for the specified Income Item.

title: CUSIP Identifier
description: Unique identifier according to the standards set by Committee on Uniform Security Identification Practices. The CUSIP is registered with the SEC and the Federal Reserve.

title: Development Stage Total Phases Count
description: Number of phases that exist in the project.

title: Employment Time In Line Of Work Years Count
description: The total number of years the borrower has been employed in that reported occupation. One source of this data is the URLA Section IV (Years Employed In This Line Of Work.)

title: Estimated Insurance Claim Amount
description: The estimated dollar amount of the insurance claim that will be filed.

title: Fee Summary Total Deposited Reserves Amount
description: The total amount of escrow reserves to be deposited.

title: Flood Depth Feet Number
description: The depth of the flood water in relation to the ground for a particular property. Measured in feet.

title: Fully Indexed Initial Principal And Interest Payment Amount
description: The dollar amount of the principal and interest payment when calculated using the loan amount and fully-indexed interest rate (in place of Note Interest Rate) to arrive at full amortization during the loan term.

title: HELOC Initial Advance Amount
description: The amount of money that a borrower receives at closing in a HELOC transaction.

title: HUD 235 Subsidy Payment Amount
description: The HUD 235 subsidy amount that is part of the total payment being reported.

title: Instrument Number Identifier
description: Sequential number assigned to each recorded document by the a County Recorder

title: Insulation Area Type
description: Indicates that the area specified by Insulation Area Type does have insulation.

title: Insulation Area Type Other Description
description: A free-form text field used to describe the location of the insulation if Other is selected as the Insulation Area Type.

title: Insulation Comment Description
description: A free-form text field for commenting on the presence or absence of insulation.

title: Insulation HERS Type
description: A value from a predefined MISMO list representing the Index developed by the Residential Energy Services Network and is a nationally recognized system by which a home's insulation energy efficiency is measured.

title: Insulation Material Type
description: A collection of values that specify the insulation material that is used in the specified Insulation Area Type.

title: Insulation Material Type Other Description
description: A free-form text field that specifies the enumeration when the value of Other is used for the Insulation Material Type.

title: Insulation Presence Type
description: Identifies the presence or absence of insulation in area as specified by the Insulation Area Type.

title: Insulation Presence Type Other Description
description: A free-form text field used to collect additional information when Other is selected for Insulation Presence Type.

title: Insulation Rating Description
description: Specifies the rating (e.g. ""R19"") of the insulation.

title: Investor Credit Policy Effective Date
description: The effective date of the investor credit policy applied to this loan.

title: Judicial Division Name
description: The name of the Judicial Division in which the subject property resides.

title: Lien Priority Type
description: A value from a MISMO prescribed list that specifies the priority of the lien against the subject property.

title: Loan Interest Accrual Start Date
description: The date that interest begins to accrue for a loan.

title: Manufactured Home Attached To Foundation Indicator
description: Indicates that the manufactured home is attached to its foundation

title: MI Comment Description
description: A free-form alpha numeric string which contains comments from the MI company regarding the loan in question.

title: Military Service Classification Type Other Description
description: A free-form text field that specifies the enumeration when the value of Other is used for Military Service Classification Type.

title: Neighborhood Acceptability Of Cooperative Ownership Description
description: A free-form text field describing how the neighborhood does accept cooperative property ownership

title: Notary Commission State Name
description: The state in which notary is commissioned.

title: Ownership Transfer Transaction Type Other Description
description: A free-form text field used to collect additional information when Other is selected for Ownership Transfer Transaction Type.

title: Parcel Identification Type
description: Specifies other parcel identification types that are used by taxing authorities or others to identify a parcel of property

title: Parcel Identification Type Other Description
description: A text field used to specify the kind of Parcel identifier when ""Other"" is selected from the enumerated list.

title: Parcel Identifier
description: The actual identifier value of the type specified by Parcel Identifier Type.

title: Parent Agency Indicator
description: When true, indicates the Housing Counseling Agency is a parent agency

title: Parking Space Identifier
description: The identification of the parking space or spaces assigned to the subject unit (e.g. space numbers).

title: Parking Spaces Count
description: Specifies the number of vehicle parking spaces for the subject unit.

title: Partial Payment Allowed Indicator
description: When true, indicates that the terms of the loan allow principal and interest payments that are less than the amount due.

title: Partial Payment Application Item Type
description: A value from a MISMO prescribed list that specifies the item to which a partial payment is to be applied.

title: Partial Payment Application Method Type
description: The method used for applying a partial payment to the loan.

title: Payoff Ordered Datetime
description: The date and time that a payoff order was submitted to the existing lien holder.

title: Pool Maximum Accrual Rate Percent
description: The maximum rate, expressed as a percent, at which interest can accrue on a pool.

title: Prepayment Penalty Summary Option Type Other Description
description: A free-form text field that specifies the enumeration when Other is selected as the Prepayment Penalty Summary Option Type.

title: Project Car Storage Description
description: Specifies the details, condition, restrictions, proximity, etc. of car storage for the entire project.

title: Property Ground Lease Expiration Date
description: The final expiration date of the ground lease.

title: Provided Service Estimated Cost Amount
description: The estimated amount of a provided service.

title: Regulation Z High Cost Loan Indicator
description: When true, indicates the loan is determined to be high cost under Regulation Z.

title: Repurchase Reason Type Other Description
description: A free-form text field that specifies the enumeration when the value of Other is used for Repurchase Reason Type.

title: Sales History Researched Indicator
description: Indicates that the sales or transfer history research of the subject property and comparable sales was performed.

title: Service Payment On Account Identifier
description: An alphanumeric designation assigned to the prepaid account to be debited for the payment.

title: Service Payment On Account Maximum Debit Amount
description: The maximum dollar amount that can be debited from the prepaid account on any single transaction.

title: Service Payment On Account Minimum Balance Amount
description: The dollar amount at which the system should send a message that the prepaid account needs to be replenished. It may also trigger the system to discontinue processing documents until more funds are added to the account.

title: Service Payment Reference Identifier
description: A unique identifier assigned to each payment transaction for tracking and auditing purposes.

title: Service Payment Secondary Credit Account Identifier
description: For credit card transactions this is an additional identifier that appears on the credit card in various locations depending on the Credit Card Type.

title: Service Product Description
description: A descriptive name for the product type, such as: Lenders Policy.

title: Service Product Identifier
description: A unique identifier that correlates to a specific request product type

title: Service Product Name Add On Description
description: A brief description of the service or product option being added to a primary service or product.

title: Service Product Name Add On Identifier
description: Some unique identifier that correlates to a specific sub-part of the product; usually a number.

title: Service Product Name Description
description: A descriptive name for the response product, such as: Super Eagle.

title: Site Estimated Value Amount
description: The dollar value estimated for the property site (e.g. land that is improved so that it is ready to be used for a specific purpose.)

title: Subordinate Financing Is New Indicator
description: When true indicates that subordinate financing is being created simultaneously with the subject loan.

title: Title Endorsement Included Indicator
description: Indicates that the Title Endorsement is included in the Title product.

title: Treasury NPV Date
description: The date on which the loan is evaluated for trial eligibility for the first time.

title: URLA Total Commissions Income Amount
description: The total of gross monthly commission income amount for all borrowers reported on an instance of the URLA. Collected on the URLA in Section V. Monthly Income.

title: Verification By Name
description: The name or initials of the person who verified information in the record.

title: 203K Consultant Identity Of Interest Statement
description: Certification letter completed by all consultants and plan reviewers who are required to sign the following certification after preparing/reviewing the work write-up and cost estimate. The signer certifies that all items requiring correction and that the rehabilitation proposal now meets all HUD requirements for 203(k) Rehabilitation Mortgage Insurance.

title: Credit Card Authorization
description: Authorizes a company to use a credit card belonging to a client for mortgage related charges. Generally these charges consist of credit report and appraisal fee.

title: IRS 1099R
description: Distributions From Pensions, Annuities, Retirement or Profit-Sharing Plans, IRAs, Insurance Contracts, etc.

title: Refinance Cost Estimate Worksheet - HECM
description: Documentation showing how the total cost of refinancing was calculated in accordance with the Anti-Churning Disclosure form to ensure that the mortgagor is not being induced to refinance his/her existing HECM without benefit to the mortgagor and/or solely for the benefit of the mortgagee.

title: Relocation Benefits Package
description: Describes terms and conditions of the relocation package.

title: Relocation Buyout Agreement
description: Establishes the terms between a relocation company and an employee to purchase a home based on the appraised value. It describes what happens if a home does not sell within a certain period (usually 60 or 90 days), and the circumstances in which a relocation company will buy a home.

title: Remittance Delivery Receipt
description: A document provided to the remitter for cash received related to the Single Family Property Disposition Program (Section 204(g)) that shows the remittance amount, case number and the date that the collection took place. HUD-235.1 (4/89).

title: Rental Agreement
description: Establishes the rights and duties of the landlord and tenant in a rental transaction. At a minimum identifies the parties, the property, the term of the rental, and the amount of rent for the term.

title: Rental Income Analysis Statement
description: Evaluates the rental potential of a property and establishes its value.

title: Repayment Plan Agreement
description: An agreement between a servicer and a borrower in which the servicer agrees not to exercise its legal right to foreclose and the borrower agrees to a payment plan that will, over a certain time period, bring the borrower current on the loan.

title: Request For Agreement Of Short Sale
description: A contract between a buyer and seller (borrower) has been reached and the borrower is requesting approval from the servicer for the short sale prior to the execution of the sales agreement. (Also known as RASS).

title: Request For Copy Of Tax Return
description: Authorizes taxing authority (such as IRS) to provide certified copy of borrowers tax return

title: Request For Copy Of Tax Return - IRS 4506
description: Request for Copy of Tax Return

title: ABA
description: American Bankers Association

title: Days On Market Description
description: The total number of continuous days from the date that a property is listed or advertised for sale through the date that it is taken off the market or contracted for sale.

title: Property Data Identifier
description: A unique identifier assigned by Fannie Mae for appraisal data collected for this loan. The party assigning the identifier can be provided using the IdentifierOwnerURI associated with a MISMO identifier.

title: Produce Other Documents
description: Process of generating the required loan disclosures and documents (other than the Loan Estimate) and providing them to the Borrower(s) within a specified number of days after application.

title: Perform Assumption Processing and Validation
description: The process of handling the assumption of an existing loan by a new party. The servicer and/or investor underwrites and approves the assumption. The servicer retains information on the original borrower and adjusts the loan information to reflect the new borrower.

title: Issuing Authority
description: See Certificate Authority. This term is also defined in the MERS® eRegistry Procedures Manual available at members.mersinc.org.

title: 20% Exchange Form
description: A form generated by the Retirement Plans case administrator when a participant exchange exceeds the 20% per year limit in exchanges out of the fixed contract.

title: 401(a) Plan
description: A trust created or organized in the United States and forming part of a stock bonus, pension, or profit-sharing plan of an employer for the exclusive benefit of his employees or their beneficiaries shall constitute a qualified trust under this section.

title: 401(k) Plan
description: A non-government employer-sponsored qualified defined contribution retirement plan which gives employees a choice of investment options, typically mutual funds.

title: 403(b) Plan
description: A type of tax-deferred retirement savings program available to employees of public schools, certain non-profits, and some members of the clergy.

title: 403(b) Withdrawal
description: Requires that the participants in a 403(b) plan are notified of the 20% federal tax penalty that may apply when making withdrawals from their 403(b).

title: 404(c)
description: The Employee Retirement Income Security Act (ERISA) Section 404(c) sets forth guidelines which all 401(k) plans must meet regarding educating employees about 401(k) plans and disclosure of plan and investment-related information to them.

title: 412(i) Plan
description: A section 412(i) plan is a tax-qualified retirement plan that is funded entirely by a life insurance contract or an annuity.

title: 415 Limit
description: In a defined contribution plan, the 415 Limit restricts the amount of contributions and forfeitures that can be made to one or more qualified defined contribution plans for the benefit of any individual participant.

title: Active Associate
description: Employee's not terminated or made inactive

title: Actively At Work
description: When an Eligible Associate is performing services for a Participating Company for any portion of the scheduled work day or is using Your Time. Except as otherwise provided for in Section 2.02.05 - Your Time Accrual During Periods of Absences - Actively-at

title: Actuary
description: A business professional who analyzes the financial consequences of risk. Uses mathematics, statistics and financial theory to study uncertain future events, especially those of concern to insurance and pension programs.

title: Acxiom
description: Third party vendor who provides pre-fill services through interactions in Commercial Internet Quoting (CIQ) for Commercial Connections (CC) projects.

title: Additional Regular (Hours)
description: Usually applicable to non-exempt associates. Overtime at the straight time rate that is processed when an associate works hours over their scheduled hours to 40 worked hours. At 40 hours, then overtime will then be calculated. Earn code OTS.

title: Adjuster
description: A person who inspects, appraises damages, investigates and settles claims with insureds and/or third party claimants.

title: Administrator
description: Person with the responsibility to maintain and operate a computer system but may also refer to the elevated privileges associated with this role.

title: Advance Commission
description: Process by which commissions are paid to a producer prior to receipt of premium.

title: Affirmative Action
description: Any program, policy or procedure that an employer implements in order to correct past discrimination and prevent current and future discrimination within the workplace.

title: Affirmative Election (Participant)
description: The active choice of an employee to participate or opt out of participating in salary reduction contributions to a retirement plan during the required timeframe allocated for enrollment.

title: Agent
description: See Insurance Agent.

title: Agent Affiliated with Corporation
description: Required attribute for DTCC Licensing & Appointments File, with valid values of Y, N or space, depending on the licensing transaction record type.

title: Agent Appointment Special Deal End Date (Special Deal Agent Appointment End Date)
description: Provides the ability to control a Special Deal at the agent appointment level. The last business calendar date on which the Special Deal is effective for a specific agent appointment.

title: Agent Number
description: A unique five digit alphanumeric code assigned to each E&S/Specialty Customer Branch Office, based on ISO state and E&S/Specialty product. Each Customer Branch Office may have multiple Agent Numbers.

title: Agent State
description: Geographical location of the Agency. As a policy attribute it can be one basis for reporting agency production.

title: Agents Required
description: The number of agents (actual and forecast) required for past time periods based on the Actual Contacts Received, Average Handle Time, and forecast objective. (Service Level, Maximum Occupancy, or Average Speed to Answer.)

title: Alien
description: Any individual who is not a U.S. citizen or U.S. national.

title: All Capitalization Fund (All Cap Fund)
description: A stock mutual fund that invests in equity securities without regard to whether a company is characterized as small, medium or large.

title: Alternative Workplace Solutions (AWS)
description: Alternatives that may be available in certain circumstances to provide scheduling and work location flexibility that best meets the needs of associates, managers, and the organization.

title: Percentage of Cost of Workforce
description: The cost of the workforce as compared to all costs can be measured by summing all salaries and dividing by the total company costs within a given period.

title: Salary Competitiveness Ratio (SCR)
description: Used to evaluate the competitiveness of compensation options. Can be determined by dividing the average company salary by the average salary offered from competitors or by the rest of your industry.

title: Healthcare Expense per Current Employee
description: Provides an understanding of the comprehensiveness of a company's health care plan. Can be determined by taking the total price of health care costs divided by all employees.

title: Benefits Satisfaction
description: This allows a company to see how satisfied an employee is with specific benefits they are offered. Can be determined through surveys, and can be used to break down each benefit individually.

title: Employee Productivity Rate
description: Helps to measure workforce efficiency over time. Can be determined by taking the total company revenue and dividing it by the total number of employees.

title: Return On Investment
description: As an organization, you want to ensure that the dollars you are putting into training your employees is paying off. Can be defined as the profit per dollar invested in social compensations/wages.

title: Employee Satisfaction Index
description: This is a key metric underlying talent retention. Using a company-wide survey can be helpful in gauging employee happiness.

title: Number of Employee Satisfaction Surveys
description: Helps understand how much effort is being put into maintaining and improving employee happiness.

title: Percent of Employees Trained in Company Culture
description: Evaluates the importance and understanding of company-wide organizational culture.

title: Percent of Vacation Days Used
description: Helps show the company attitude toward a healthy work-life balance. Determined by observing the number of vacation days used as compared to those unused.

title: Net Promotor Score
description: Measures how likely an employee is to recommend their organization as a place to work. This is determined by the difference in percentage of promotors and detractors.

title: Absenteeism Rate
description: Gives perspective on the amount of labor and productivity lost due to sickness and otherwise unpredicted leave. Formula: (Total number of lost workdays due to absence) / (Number of available workdays in an organization) = (Absenteeism rate)

title: Number of Full Time Employees
description: Keeps tabs on the growth of the company workforce over time.

title: Number of Contractors
description: Examines the growth in associated workers over time. Can be compared to the number of full-time workers to better understand workforce trends.

title: Average Tenure
description: The average length of time that an employee spends with the company helps determine employee satisfaction and talent retention.

title: Voluntary Termination Rate
description: Determined by taking the number of employee-led resignations from the company over the total number of terminations in a given time period.

title: Involuntary Termination Rate
description: Determined by taking the number of employer-led resignations from the company over the total number of terminations in a given time period.

title: Retirement Rate
description: This metric is particularly important for any organization developing a strategic workforce plan. Can be calculated by looking at the number of employees who retired as a percentage of the headcount.

title: Average Age Of Retirement
description: The summed age of all retiring employees divided by the number of retiring employees. Being aware of these trends aid in forecasting retirement and planning for workforce replacement.

title: New Hire 90-Day Failure Rate
description: Helps determine how successful the talent acquisition process is at finding the right fit for jobs.

title: First Year Voluntary Termination Rate
description: Reflects on how welcoming the company is to new hires. A high percentage suggests that the right people are being hired, but not embraced.

title: Average Time to Fill a Job Vacancy
description: Tracks how efficient the hiring process is in terms of time resources used to fill a vacant spot.

title: Hiring Process Satisfaction Rate
description: Provides perspective on how well the process works from the employee’s perspective.

title: Cost Per Hire
description: Acknowledges the amount of resources invested into acquiring the best talent. Can be determined by averaging the total marketing, hiring process, and referral (if necessary) costs per hire.

title: Effectiveness of Training
description: Helps the company understand how comfortable new hires feel after their training vs. before. Typically determined through a post-training survey.

title: Training Cost per Employee
description: Helps to measure the amount invested in onboarding new hires.

title: Percent of Employees Trained
description: Helps a company see how quickly new hires are being onboarded.

title: Diversity Rate
description: Workplace diversity helps to cultivate innovation and competitive advantage. Diversity of nationalities and ethnicities can be calculated by noting the differences among employee demographic segments.

title: Number of D&I Initiatives Implemented
description: The number of D&I initiatives implemented measures organizational commitment to establishing and maintaining a culture of diversity and inclusion.

title: Attrition Rate
description: Helps a company figure out how successful they are at retaining talent. Determined by dividing the number of employees who left the company in a given period by the average number of employees in that time period.

title: Turnover Rate For Highest Performers
description: Turnover of top performers in particular is negative and comes at a higher cost. This metric helps indicates the success of retention efforts and aids planning for talent replacement. Can be determined by dividing the number of high performers to leave in the past year by total high performers identified.

title: Average Time to Find a Hire
description: Helps track the efficiency of the hiring process.

title: Candidates Interviewed per Hire
description: Determined by calculating the total number of candidates interviewed by the total number of hires in a particular hiring period.

title: Yield Percentage
description: This is the percentage of candidates remaining after each round of elimination in the hiring process. A low percentage might indicate the need to update an unclear or unattractive job posting, and a high percentage indicates a larger number of qualified candidates with whom to continue the hiring process.

title: Knowledge Achieved With Training
description: Helps the company see not specifically the price of the training, but whether it was effective. Seeing if the individuals retained knowledge well enough to apply it is critical. Can be determined by creating an exam, and monitoring exam pass rate %, average score %, and pre/post training %.

title: Diversity Numbers/Nationalities In The Work Force
description: Workplace diversity helps to cultivate innovation and competitive advantage. Diversity of nationalities and ethnicities can be calculated by noting the differences among employee demographic segments.

title: Acceptance Rate
description: Dividing the number of acceptances by the number of offers allows organizations to get a sense of how successful their recruitment strategies are. Industry benchmarks can then be a helpful comparison.

title: Percent of Job Candidates who Meet Job Criteria
description: Helps in evaluating the effectiveness of job postings in reaching top candidates.

title: Rate of Internal Job Hires
description: Shows the effectiveness of organizational talent development.

title: Rate of Internal Referral Hires
description: Allows managers to see the value added when current employees help to identify and acquire talent.

title: Performance of New Hires
description: The performance of new hires can be compared to that of other employees. Typically done by evaluating performance reports.

title: Internal Promotions Vs. External Hires
description: This ratio measures how many people already working at a company are considered for internal promotion versus the number of externally attracted people. Can be particularly effective when looking at organizational succession planning.

title: Internal Promotion Rate
description: Internal promotions indicate successful retention and growth of top performers. Can be determined by dividing the number of promoted individuals by the total number of employees.

title: Suggestions per Employee
description: Evaluates employee engagement in improving business processes, and reflects on the openness of a company to employee input.

title: HR-To-FTE Ratio
description: The number of HR full time equivalents divided by the total number of full time equivalents. Helps determine HR's ability to provide services. Larger organizations typically have a smaller ratio, but more HR staff overall, than small businesses.

title: Cycle Time To Process Payroll
description: Shows timeframe of process, giving projection if assistance/updated process is needed. This is the number of business days in the payroll process from start to finish.

title: Cycle Time To Resolve Payroll Errors
description: The number of business days it takes to resolve payroll error reported by employees. A high number of days could indicate the need to review your payroll process.

title: Percentage of Workforce below Performance Standards
description: This measure keeps tab on the amount of low-performing employees in an organization.

title: Acceptable Downtime
description: Maximum elapsed time between a disruption and restoration of needed operational capacity or capability.

title: Acceptable Risk
description: The level of Residual Risk that has been determined to be a reasonable level of potential loss/disruption for a specific IT system.

title: Access Authorization Tool (AAT)
description: NI Systems software used to set user access rights (e.g. rights of primary agent vs. office admin).

title: Access Control
description: Ensures that resources are made available only to authorized users, programs, processes, and systems. Rules for access are defined by policies and attributes.

title: Access Control List (ACL)
description: A mechanism that implements access control for a system resource by listing the identities of the system entities that are permitted to access the resource.

title: Access De-Provisioning
description: The process of removing authorized access†from†an application/system. Generally as the result of leaving the organization or a change in responsibilities.

title: Access Provisioning
description: The process of granting authorized access to an application/system.

title: Access Recertification
description: The process of verifying and approving that existing access is required and appropriate.††This process performed by an associate HR leader within Sailpoint IIQ.††

title: Account Recoverability
description: Accounts in nwie.net domain of Active Directory that are recoverable by cracking account password

title: ACORD 102 Message
description: The ACORD XML Message Structure for a post-issue Fund Transfer transaction.

title: ACORD 105 Message (105 message Full Surrender)
description: The ACORD XML Message Structure for a withdrawal transaction.

title: ACORD 107 Message
description: The ACORD XML Message Structure for a post-issue Arrangements transaction.

title: ACORD 1241 Message
description: The ACORD Message which defines the Product Profile for Annuity Lite File, also referred to as the DTCC Fee and Expense Transmittal File. See DTCC Product Profile for Annuity Lite File.

title: ACORD 212 Message
description: The ACORD XML Message Structure for a Values Inquiry transaction.

title: ACORD Message
description: The structure and content of the group of electronic data interchange file records which define a specific insurance business process supported by ACORD standards.

title: Activation
description: The implementation of business continuity procedures, activities and plans in response to a serious incident, emergency, event or crisis.

title: Actuarial Research Commercial Area Data Environment (ARCADE)
description: Hierarchical database located in the IDM_Commercial space on Teradata containing PCIO, HV, and Policy Center data from multiple sources built to support advanced analytics for Standard Commercial.

title: Ad Hoc Claims Reporting System (ACRS)
description: Mainframe system which provides the regional customer on-line access to all suit and non suit related data currently stored on the Legal Processing system (LPS) database. Will be replaced by ClaimCenter.

title: Advanced Encryption Standard  (AES)
description: A U.S. Government-approved cryptographic algorithm that can be used to protect electronic data. The AES algorithm is a symmetric block cipher that can encrypt (encipher) and decrypt (decipher) information

title: Advanced Persistent Threat (APT)
description: An adversary that possesses sophisticated levels of expertise and significant resources which allow it to create opportunities to achieve its objectives using multiple attack vectors (NIST SP800-61). Scope Notes: The APT: 1. pursues its objectives repeate

title: Agency Anywhere (AA)
description: A browser-based client application that provides an interface to Agency-related IT systems.

title: Agency Cross Reference (XREF)
description: A system of reference which brings together Distribution Partner (agency / firm and producer) data from multiple systems across the Enterprise and identifies relationships between agency / firm and producer codes from the various source systems.

title: Agency Management Integration (AMI)
description: An Agency Management System (AMS) application used to input customer information from purchased agencies for Agent Online Automation Plus (AOA+). Input only.

title: Agency Management System (AMS)
description: Authoritative source of record for licensing, contracting, biographical and profile data for Titan agencies and producers. AMS also stores records for Exclusive, Allied, Service Center, and NSS agencies/producers to process policies on the Titan platform.

title: Agency Management System (AMS) Vendor Software
description: Third Party or in house developed software used by independent Distribution Partner Organizations to manage their agency/brokerage operations. Interfaces with Carriers using ACORD standards or proprietary formats.

title: Agency Network (AGC)
description: A Traditional Life policy data on-line inquiry system. The system additionally provides inquiry to certain basic Variable Universal Life (VUL) policy data.

title: Agent Appointment Special Deal Start Date (Special Deal Agent Appointment Start Date)
description: Provides the ability to control a Special Deal at the agent appointment level. The business calendar date on which the Special Deal becomes effective for a specific agent appointment.

title: Agent Claims Partnership (ACP)
description: Claims interface for agencies that allows claims and payment information to be entered by agents and forwarded to Claims Processing System (CPS). Handles auto/fire claims less than or equal to $2,500.

title: Agent Information Management System (AIMS)
description: The NF system of record for firm, agent, and advisor information. The primary purpose is to track and manage licensing, appointment, and registration information for NF Producers, and General Agent Agreements for Firms.

title: Agent Master File (AMF)
description: The system that is the authoritative source for licensing, contracting, biographical, and profile data for Allied independent agencies and producers. It also manages data for producers on other systems to process policies on the Des Moines platform.

title: Agent/Staff Profile Tool (APT)
description: Interface that allows the agency to update their office info in real time. Updates the Producer Data System (PDS).

title: Agile
description: An interactive project methodology where requirements are prioritized and delivered in multiple increments, or iterations. This also involves frequent reassessment and adaptation of plans.

title: Allied Agent Center (AAC)
description: Website for agent access, used for inquiry and policy entry (quote and policy issuance).

title: Alternate Site
description: A site held in readiness for use during a business continuity invocation to continue the urgent and important processes of an organization. Alternate sites may be known as 'cold', 'warm' or 'hot.'

title: Amazon Elastic MapReduce (Amazon EMR)
description: A managed cluster platform that simplifies running big data frameworks on AWS to process and analyze vast amounts of data.

title: Amazon Simple Storage Service (Amazon S3)
description: An object storage service that offers industry-leading scalability, data availability, security, and performance.

title: Amazon Web Services (AWS)
description: A secure cloud services platform, offering computing power, database storage, content delivery and other functionality to help businesses scale and grow.

title: Transaction Layer Security (TLS)
description: Transaction layer security — a converged protocol, a revision of SSL, which offers increased security mechanisms within the protocol, developed jointly by Microsoft and Netscape.

title: Transaction Set
description: The name given to a complete trading document sent via electronic data interchange (EDI). Examples of mortgage-related documents which might be transmitted via EDI include loan applications, credit reports and appraisals.

title: Wrapping
description: To use an Encryption Key to authenticate the combination of an electronic record and existing electronic signatures associated with that electronic record, or to detect alterations to the combination of the electronic record and the prior electronic signatures, or to authenticate or detect alterations in a package of multiple electronic records.

title: X12 Data Standards
description: The uniform standards for the electronic interchange of business documents developed by the American National Standards Institute. EDI transaction sets are developed using these standards.

title: X-Mark Signature
description: The signature made by a person who is unable to sign their name. This type of signature is only legally valid when witnessed by another person.

title: XML Schemas
description: XML Schemas express shared vocabularies and support rules based application processing. They provide a means for defining the structure, content and semantics of XML documents.

title: Xpath
description: A roadmap in XML that specifies exact data points to follow.

title: ACH ABA Routing and Transit Identifier
description: 9 digit routing and transit number for the bank from which the payment is drafted

title: ACH Account Type
description: The account type from which the payment is drafted

title: ACH Additional Escrow Amount
description: Dollar amount beyond the normal PITI that is be drafted and applied to the escrow account.

title: ACH Additional Principal Amount
description: Dollar amount beyond the normal PITI that is be drafted and applied to reduce the principal of the loan.

title: ACH Bank Account Identifier
description: The number identifying the account from which the payment is drafted

title: ACH Bank Account Purpose Type
description: Identifies the purpose of the account where the payment or refund is drafted.

title: ACH Bank Account Purpose Type Other Description
description: A free-form text field used to collect additional information when Other is selected for ACH Bank Account Purpose Type.

title: ACH Draft After Due Date Day Count
description: The number of days past the payment due date that payment drafting is scheduled to occur. Payment due date plus ACH Draft Days after Due Date equals draft date.

title: ACH Draft Frequency Type
description: A value from a MISMO defined list that indicates how frequently the servicer drafts the scheduled mortgage payment from the account of the borrower.

title: ACH Draft Frequency Type Additional Description
description: A free-form text field used to provide a supplemental comment or remark regarding the ACH Draft Frequency Type.

title: ACH Draft Frequency Type Other Description
description: A free-form text field used to collect additional information when Other is selected for ACH Draft Frequency Type.
